<html>    
<head>      
<title> Myanmar to Nurture Foreign Currency Market 
</title>      
</head>      
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF">      
<table border=0 cellpadding=6>      
<tr>      
<td><h1>      
Myanmar to Nurture Foreign Currency Market</h1></td>      
</table>      
    
       12/09/96<p>
     
Ten local private entrepreneurs have been authorized to open 
     counters for sale and purchase of foreign exchange certificates (fecs) at the 
     Yangon Fec Exchange Center to nurture a foreign currency market, official paper 
     the new light of Myanmar reported today.  The fec, which is equivalent to the US 
     dollar in value and lawfully circulated on the Myanmar market, was introduced in 
     february 1993 for the convenience of foreigners visiting and doing business in 
     Myanmar since hard currency is not allowed for circulation in the country.  
     since local Myanmar nationals are also allowed to hold fecs, the use of them has 
     become widespread following the opening of the fec exchange center in 
     december last year.  
<p>The center was set up in Yangon to effect easy, legal 
     transactions of fecs and their use in the market, eliminate the practice of offering 
     lower prices to the buyers and sellers, nurture a foreign currency market 
     and do away with unsightly, illegal transactions on roadsides, the paper said.  
     the market exchange rate of the us dollar or fec with the Myanmar currency kyat 
     is 1 to 160, while its official rate is about 6, the paper added.
          <hr>
