<center>

<h1>

The Ashgabat Ecology Club
</h1></center>

<table><tr><td width=125></td><td>

<blockquote>
The Ashgabat Ecology Club is the sole non-profit provider of Internet connectivity in Turkmenistan.  At 
present, the club serves 150 clients, of whom 40 are commercial.  The club provides services to 
commercial clients at one-half the rate charged by the only other server in Turkmenistan, and its 
commercial revenues allow it to provide services free of charge to individual and non-profit users.
<p> 
The club has 3 Pentium computers which provide full cross-platform access to dial-up customers from all 
over Turkmenistan.  It also houses a publicly accessible database geared towards general use.  Because it 
has no constant connection to the Web, it receives email from Glasnet in Moscow every three hours.
<p>
<b>Ashgabat Ecology Club</b><br>
Andrey Aranbaev, Co-Chair<br>
7/2 Pavlov Street, Ashgabat 744012<br>
Tel: (3632) 353516, 351531 (office)<br>
(3632) 350257<br>
E-mail: <a href="mailto:catoffs@cat.glasnet.ru"><b> catoffs@cat.glasnet.ru</b></a><b>(office)</b><br>
<a href="mailto:catena@glas.apc.org"><b> catena@glas.apc.org</b></a><b>(Aranbaev, 
personal)</b><br>
</blockquote>
</td></tr></table>

