<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     FRANCE BECOMES CO-CHAIR OF KARABAKH NEGOTIATIONS. The OSCE has named <br>
     France as the new co-chair of the deadlocked negotiations on the <br>
     Nagorno-Karabakh dispute, RFE/RL reported on 7 January. France, <br>
     beating out an active U.S. bid, succeeds Finland, which held the <br>
     office for 20 months. The other co-chair is Russia, whose post is <br>
     permanent. The chief French negotiator will be Jacques Blot. -- Lowell <br>
     Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
