<!-- body="start" -->
     HIGH-RANKING IRANIAN DELEGATION IN ARMENIA. An Iranian delegation <br>
     headed by First Vice-President Hasan Habibi concluded a four-day visit <br>
     to Armenia on 28 December, Noyan Tapan reported. The two sides pledged <br>
     to boost bilateral cooperation in  communications, energy and <br>
     industry. Habibi, the highest-ranking Iranian official to visit <br>
     Armenia since 1991, said the current state of Armenian-Iranian <br>
     relationships is "at the desired level," ITAR-TASS reported. Armenian <br>
     President Levon Ter- Petrossyan described Iran's policy in the <br>
     Transcaucasus as "balanced" and a "stability factor" in the region. <br>
     According to Prime-Minister Armen Sarkisyan, the two countries have <br>
     "great" potential for further cooperation. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
