<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI - 19DEC96 - TRIALS ON POST-ELECTION UNREST IN YEREVAN T</title>
<h1>OMRI - 19DEC96 - TRIALS ON POST-ELECTION UNREST IN YEREVAN T</h1>
<i>fsu@mail.sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 19 Dec 96 12:59:56 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#91">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#91">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#91">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#91">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0092.html">ctroy@mail.sorosny.org: "Interfax 20Dec96 Armemnian Nuclear Safety Key  in EBRD Talks"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0090.html">fsu@mail.sorosny.org: "OMRI - 18DEC96 - FREEDOM HOUSE REPORT NOTES LACK OF HUMAN RI"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     TRIALS ON POST-ELECTION UNREST IN YEREVAN TO START IN JANUARY. An <br>
     Armenian opposition representative, Vladimir Hakhverdyan, said that <br>
     the investigation into the 25 September protests in Yerevan is <br>
     complete and that trials will begin in January, Groong reported on 18 <br>
     December citing Asbarez-on-line. The protests were triggered by <br>
     reports of alleged vote- rigging in the 22 September presidential <br>
     election. A number of supporters of the defeated opposition candidate <br>
     Vazgen Manukyan burst into the parliament building and took the <br>
     National Assembly speaker and his deputy hostage. According to <br>
     Hakhverdyan, a group of opposition activists arrested in connection <br>
     with the unrest, have been charged with inciting mass disorder and <br>
     illegally possessing arms. * Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
