<!-- body="start" -->
     ARMENIAN CHURCH HEAD MEETS WITH POPE. Pope John Paul II said he hopes <br>
     the Armenian Apostolic Church and the Roman Catholic Church will <br>
     eventually reunite, after meeting with Supreme Patriarch and <br>
     Catholicos of All Armenians Garegin I in the Vatican on 11 December, <br>
     Reuters reported. The independent Armenian church split from the <br>
     Vatican in the 5th century. Garegin said he is praying for the <br>
     pontiff's health for "the good of all humanity." -- Emil Danielyan<br>
