<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI - 5DEC96 -ENERGY TARIFFS TO RISE IN ARMENIA</title>
<h1>OMRI - 5DEC96 -ENERGY TARIFFS TO RISE IN ARMENIA</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 05 Dec 96 14:24:14 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#83">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#83">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#83">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#83">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0084.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 9DEC96 - RUSSIAN BORDER TROOP COMMANDER IN ARMENIA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0082.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 4DEC96 - LAST-MINUTE OSCE COMPROMISE ON NAGORNO-KARAB"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     ENERGY TARIFFS TO RISE IN ARMENIA. Prime Minister Armen Sarkisyan on 4 <br>
     December said the government will raise energy tariffs by 40% starting <br>
     in January, Noyan Tapan reported the same day. Sarkisyan said the <br>
     decision was taken in accordance with the 4 March agreement with the <br>
     World Bank which made its loans to Armenia contingent on bringing <br>
     energy prices closer to world ones. Armenia has undergone severe <br>
     energy shortages and winter rationing since the war in <br>
     Nagorno-Karabakh broke out in 1992. The crisis has been substantially <br>
     alleviated by the reopening of the Medzamor nuclear plant in summer <br>
     1995. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0084.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 9DEC96 - RUSSIAN BORDER TROOP COMMANDER IN ARMENIA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0082.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 4DEC96 - LAST-MINUTE OSCE COMPROMISE ON NAGORNO-KARAB"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
