<!-- body="start" -->
     ARMENIAN OPPOSITION PARTY'S OFFICE REOPENED. The office of the <br>
     National Democratic Union (AZhM) was reopened on 25 November. It was <br>
     sealed on 25 September by police following violent protests by <br>
     opposition supporters against the official results of the presidential <br>
     election. An AZhM representative told Noyan Tapan that the office <br>
     suffered serious material damage and that the party's property has not <br>
     yet been returned by the Interior Ministry. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
