<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI - 25Nov96 - KOCHARYAN REELECTED PRESIDENT OF NAGORNO-KA</title>
<h1>OMRI - 25Nov96 - KOCHARYAN REELECTED PRESIDENT OF NAGORNO-KA</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Mon, 02 Dec 96 11:34:43 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#75">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#75">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#75">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#75">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0076.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 25Nov96 - ARMENIAN OPPOSITION DEMANDS FRESH PRESIDENT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0074.html">fsu@mail.sorosny.org: "INTERFAX -- 25 Nov, Kocharian reportedly wins Karabakh vote"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     KOCHARYAN REELECTED PRESIDENT OF NAGORNO-KARABAKH. The presidential <br>
     election in Nagorno-Karabakh took place on 24 November despite its <br>
     condemnation by Azerbaijan, Russia, and major Western countries, <br>
     Western agencies reported. According to the Central Electoral <br>
     Commission in Stepanakert, 76% of the region's 89,000 voters turned <br>
     out. Robert Kocharyan, the incumbent president of the self-proclaimed <br>
     Nagorno- Karabakh Republic, who was opposed by two other candidates, <br>
     won a decisive victory, Radio France Internationale reported on 25 <br>
     November. Meanwhile, mass rallies were held in Azerbaijan to protest <br>
     the election, ITAR-TASS reported on 24 November. Turan quoted <br>
     Azerbaijani President Heydar Aliev as saying that his country will <br>
     never recognize the vote. Aliev said that besides Armenia some <br>
     unspecified countries also "support separatists in Nagorno-Karabakh." <br>
     -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0076.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 25Nov96 - ARMENIAN OPPOSITION DEMANDS FRESH PRESIDENT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0074.html">fsu@mail.sorosny.org: "INTERFAX -- 25 Nov, Kocharian reportedly wins Karabakh vote"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
