<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: INTERFAX -- 25 Nov, Kocharian reportedly wins Karabakh vote</title>
<h1>INTERFAX -- 25 Nov, Kocharian reportedly wins Karabakh vote</h1>
<i>fsu@mail.sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Tue, 26 Nov 96 18:10:56 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#74">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#74">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#74">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#74">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0075.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 25Nov96 - KOCHARYAN REELECTED PRESIDENT OF NAGORNO-KA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0073.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 22Nov96 - Armenian Constitutional Court Rejects Oppos"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
       ROBERT KOCHARIAN REPORTEDLY ELECTED KARABAKH PRESIDENT<br>
     <br>
                    STEPANAKERT, Nov 25 (Interfax) - According to <br>
     preliminary reports, current  president of  the  self-proclaimed  <br>
     Nagorno-<br>
               Karabakh Republic  Robert Kocharian  was re-elected  <br>
     president<br>
               November 24.<br>
                    Kocharian won  86.11% of  the votes,  the  local  <br>
     central<br>
               electoral commission  told Interfax.  Next came  Deputy of <br>
     the<br>
               Karabakh parliament Boris Arushunian (6.9%) and in third <br>
     place<br>
               leader of the local Communist Party Grant Melkumian (3.7%).<br>
                    The same  source said  that turnout  stood at  78% <br>
     (about<br>
     <br>
               90,000 voters).  International observers,  including <br>
     observers<br>
               from  Russia,  the  U.S.,  Canada,  Switzerland,  Germany  <br>
     and<br>
               Slovenia, did  not reveal  any serious  violations  of  <br>
     voting<br>
               procedure, said the Central Electoral Commission.<br>
                    Kocharian was  born in  Stepanakert in 1954. He <br>
     graduated<br>
               from the  Yerevan Polytechnic  Institute in Armenia. From <br>
     1980<br>
               onwards he  held various  posts in the Communist Party and <br>
     the<br>
               Young Communist League in the then Nagorno-Karabakh <br>
     Autonomous<br>
               Region of  Azerbaijan. In  1994 he became the head of <br>
     Nagorno-<br>
               Karabakh's State  Defense Committee.  On December 22, 1994, <br>
     he<br>
               was elected president of Karabakh by the Karabakh <br>
     parliament.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0075.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 25Nov96 - KOCHARYAN REELECTED PRESIDENT OF NAGORNO-KA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0073.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 22Nov96 - Armenian Constitutional Court Rejects Oppos"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
