<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI - 21Nov96 - European Parliament Condemns Presidential E</title>
<h1>OMRI - 21Nov96 - European Parliament Condemns Presidential E</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 21 Nov 96 11:39:06 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#72">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#72">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#72">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#72">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0073.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 22Nov96 - Armenian Constitutional Court Rejects Oppos"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0071.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 20Nov96 - Armenian Constitutional Court Hearings Inte"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT CONDEMNS PRESIDENTIAL ELECTION IN ARMENIA. The <br>
     European Parliament has passed a resolution challenging the legitimacy <br>
     of the 22 September Armenian presidential election and calling for a <br>
     new round of elections to be held in those electoral districts where <br>
     serious violations took place, Noyan Tapan reported on 20 November. <br>
     The resolution condemned the crackdown on the opposition and the media <br>
     and called on the Armenian government to adhere to democratic <br>
     principles. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0073.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 22Nov96 - Armenian Constitutional Court Rejects Oppos"</a>
