<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI - 20Nov96 - Nagorno-Karabakh Negotiation Update</title>
<h1>OMRI - 20Nov96 - Nagorno-Karabakh Negotiation Update</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Wed, 20 Nov 96 10:14:20 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#70">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#70">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#70">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#70">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0071.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 20Nov96 - Armenian Constitutional Court Hearings Inte"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0069.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 19Nov96 - Opposition Rally in Yerevan"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     NAGORNO-KARABAKH NEGOTIATION UPDATE. Acting Armenian presidential <br>
     spokesman Levon Zurabyan said that Azerbaijan has refused to <br>
     participate further in drafting a joint declaration of principles on a <br>
     settlement of the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict, RFE/RL reported on 19 <br>
     November. The declaration was due to be presented at the OSCE's <br>
     December summit in Lisbon. Zurabyan said Armenia will not sign any <br>
     documents at the summit unless all sides agree on them in advance. <br>
     Meanwhile, another round of Nagorno-Karabakh peace talks sponsored by <br>
     the OSCE Minsk group began in Helsinki on 18 November, Noyan Tapan and <br>
     Turan reported. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0071.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 20Nov96 - Armenian Constitutional Court Hearings Inte"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0069.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 19Nov96 - Opposition Rally in Yerevan"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
