<!-- body="start" -->
     NAGORNO-KARABAKH ELECTION UPDATE. The leader of the self-proclaimed <br>
     Republic of Nagorno-Karabakh, Robert Kocharyan, called on residents of <br>
     the region to take part in the 24 November presidential election, <br>
     Noyan Tapan reported on 12 November. During one of his campaign <br>
     speeches, Kocharyan said the recognition of Nagorno-Karabakh as an <br>
     equal side to the conflict by the OSCE and creation of a strong army <br>
     are among the biggest achievements of his government. According to <br>
     Kocharyan, the development of small and medium-sized enterprises and <br>
     tax privileges for agriculture will remedy Karabakh's economic <br>
     hardships. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
