<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI - 12Nov96 - Ter-Petrossyan Inaugurated Amid Controversy</title>
<h1>OMRI - 12Nov96 - Ter-Petrossyan Inaugurated Amid Controversy</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Tue, 12 Nov 96 10:29:20 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#64">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#64">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#64">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#64">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0065.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "CENASIAN  BATTALIN  MAY  BACK  KARABAKH PEACEKEEPING  EFFORT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0063.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 11Nov96 - Armenian Opposition Leader Ends Hunger Stri"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     TER-PETROSSYAN INAUGURATED AMID CONTROVERSY. Armenian President Levon <br>
     Ter-Petrossyan was inaugurated for a second five-year term on 11 <br>
     November, Armenian and Western media reported. The OSCE questioned the <br>
     vote results of the disputed 22 September presidential election, while <br>
     the opposition National Accord bloc (AHD) still claims it was robbed <br>
     of the victory. The ceremony, which was boycotted by the AHD deputies, <br>
     took place two days before the Constitutional Court is to start <br>
     hearings on the opposition's appeal to annul the election results. The <br>
     defeated AHD candidate, Vazgen Manukyan, described Ter-Petrossyan's <br>
     decision to take the oath before the court's ruling as a "violation of <br>
     ethical principles." According to Reuters, "Ter-Petrossyan looked <br>
     grave and seemed to have lost weight." Meanwhile, there were no <br>
     results yet from the 10 November local elections. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0065.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "CENASIAN  BATTALIN  MAY  BACK  KARABAKH PEACEKEEPING  EFFORT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0063.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 11Nov96 - Armenian Opposition Leader Ends Hunger Stri"</a>
