<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
 <br>
 <br>
 FINAL RESULTS OF ARMENIAN ELECTIONS. The Armenian Central Election Commission <br>
 released the final results of the 22 September presidential polls, confirming <br>
 the victory of the incumbent Levon Ter-Petrossyan with 52.75% of the vote, <br>
 ITAR-TASS reported on 22 October. The opposition, whose candidate, Vazgen <br>
 Manukyan, won 41.3% of the vote, has accused the authorities of election <br>
 rigging and plans to appeal the official results to the Constitutional Court. <br>
 -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
