<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI--Oct 18 1996--ARMENIAN OPPOSITION RALLY BANNED</title>
<h1>OMRI--Oct 18 1996--ARMENIAN OPPOSITION RALLY BANNED</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Fri, 18 Oct 96 11:33:55 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#42">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#42">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#42">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#42">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0043.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI-22 Oct. 1996- OPPOSITION PARTY IN LOCAL ELECTION BOYCOT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0041.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI--16 Oct 1996--INT'L OBSERVERS CRITICIZE ARMEN ELECTION"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     <br>
     ARMENIAN OPPOSITION RALLY BANNED. The Yerevan city authorities <br>
     reversed themselves and withdrew permission for opposition rallies <br>
     slated for 18 October, citing errors in the application, Noyan Tapan <br>
     and RFE/RL reported the same day. The opposition said that they will <br>
     apply for the demonstration to be held next week. The move follows <br>
     President Levon Ter-Petrossyan's 11 October decree lifting the ban on <br>
     public gatherings that was imposed after the 25 September violence in <br>
     the capital. In other news, chief presidential aide Gerard Libaridian <br>
     charged that the OSCE used the 22 September presidential elections to <br>
     force Armenia to make concessions in the negotiations over the <br>
     Nagorno-Karabakh conflict, Noyan Tapan reported. Libaridian accused <br>
     the OSCE observer mission monitoring the vote of "playing political <br>
     games," and said the latter misinterpreted Armenian electoral laws. <br>
     The mission questioned the official election results according to <br>
     which Ter-Petrossyan won a second term. -- Emil Danielyan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0043.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI-22 Oct. 1996- OPPOSITION PARTY IN LOCAL ELECTION BOYCOT"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0041.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI--16 Oct 1996--INT'L OBSERVERS CRITICIZE ARMEN ELECTION"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
