<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     ARMENIAN ELECTION UPDATE. Three candidates have withdrawn from the 22 <br>
     September presidential election and thrown their support behind <br>
     National Democratic Union leader Vazgen Manukyan, Western and Russian <br>
     agencies reported on 17 September. The now four-way presidential race <br>
     pits Communist leader Sergei Badalyan and Scientific-Industrial Civic <br>
     Union leader Ashot Manucharyan against Manukyan and incumbent Levon <br>
     Ter- Petrossyan. Long the clear favorite, Ter-Petrossyan is now widely <br>
     perceived to be facing a serious challenge from Manukyan. -- Lowell <br>
     Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
