<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI--4 September 96--ELECTIONS SCHEDULED IN NAGORNO-KARABAK</title>
<h1>OMRI--4 September 96--ELECTIONS SCHEDULED IN NAGORNO-KARABAK</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Wed, 04 Sep 96 12:45:31 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#11">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#11">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#11">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#11">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0012.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--6 September 96--HEAD OF ARMENIAN STATE RADIO DISMISSED"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0010.html">eurasia@mail.sorosny.org: "OMRI--30 August 1996--CONFUSION OVER GERMAN STANCE"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     ELECTIONS SCHEDULED IN NAGORNO-KARABAKH . . . At a session marking the <br>
     fifth anniversary of the Republic of Nagorno Karabakh's (RNK) <br>
     unilateral declaration of independence from Azerbaijan, the RNK <br>
     parliament voted to hold a presidential election on 24 November 1996, <br>
     according to a 30 August Armenian Radio report monitored by the BBC. <br>
     The current RNK president, Robert Kocharyan, was elected in 1994; his <br>
     term expires in December 1996. Under the terms of the Law on <br>
     Presidential Elections passed by the RNK parliament in May 1996, the <br>
     new president will be elected for five years; presidential candidates <br>
     must collect a minimum of 1,500 signatures in their support from <br>
     residents of at least four of the six raions of the RNK. -- Liz Fuller<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
