<!-- body="start" -->
     ARMENIA HEAVILY DEPENDENT ON FOREIGN AID. Armenia received $200 <br>
     million worth of foreign aid in 1995, Finansovye izvestiya reported on <br>
     27 August, citing Armenian Banking Association President Tigran <br>
     Sarkisiyan. The U.S. alone delivered $122 million last year and $85 <br>
     million so far this year. Last year, the World Bank granted the <br>
     country $562 million in loans and the IMF gave $118 million. In 1995, <br>
     Armenian GDP was an estimated $1.3 billion. -- Peter Rutland in Moscow<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
