<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Armenia: OMRI--16 August 96--IMF SATISFIED WITH REFORMS IN ARMENIA</title>
<h1>OMRI--16 August 96--IMF SATISFIED WITH REFORMS IN ARMENIA</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Fri, 16 Aug 96 13:40:18 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#3">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#3">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#3">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#3">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0004.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--21 August 96--FBI IN TRANSCAUCASUS AND CENTRAL ASIA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0002.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--14 August 96--ASTRONOMER AMBARTSUMYAN DIES"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     IMF SATISFIED WITH REFORMS IN ARMENIA . . . Tanas Katsanbas, deputy <br>
     director of the IMF's Second European Division, said in Yerevan on 7 <br>
     August that he is satisfied with the progress of economic reform in <br>
     Armenia. The government's macroeconomic stabilization measures have <br>
     resulted in an annual real GDP growth rate of 4%, while monthly <br>
     inflation rates have fallen to 2-3%, Snark reported. Katsanbas also <br>
     pointed to a range of problems, including enterprise fiscal arrears <br>
     and credit shortages, but noted that those problems can be resolved <br>
     through fiscal reform. Katsanbas also argued that Armenian industries <br>
     must be restructured in order to improve export competitiveness <br>
     abroad, and stressed the importance of joining the WTO. -- Aghasi <br>
     Yenokian in Yerevan<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0004.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--21 August 96--FBI IN TRANSCAUCASUS AND CENTRAL ASIA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0002.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--14 August 96--ASTRONOMER AMBARTSUMYAN DIES"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
