<title>Groong Network: From Snark Homepage</title>
<h1>From Snark Homepage</h1>
martiros (<i>martiros@scf-fs.usc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 10 Jan 97 18:41:10 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#328">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#328">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#328">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#328">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0329.html">Noyan Tapan: "Noyan Tapan Bulletin 09/01/97"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0327.html">H.TCHILINGIRIAN@lse.ac.uk: "Religion in Azerbaijan"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     NO CASUALTIES FROM NATURAL CALAMITY RECORDED IN ARMENIA OVER<br>
1996<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 7. (SNARK). The Armenian Department on Emergencies<br>
informed Snark that two floods, 3 landslides, 4 hails and several<br>
forest fires were recorded over 1996, in Armenia. About 80<br>
earthquakes measuring 7 on the 12th scale were recorded by the<br>
seismic monitory station. Two hurricanes in February and December<br>
caused great damage. Meanwhile, no casualties were recorded over 1996<br>
against seven lives that have been lost in 1995 and eight lives in<br>
1994.<br>
     No incidents were recorded at the Armenian railway, air lines<br>
and at the main energetic sites. The main gas pipeline halted its<br>
activity for 25 days because of organizational and technical reasons.<br>
     Explosions, car and other accidents resulted in 25 casualties<br>
recorded in Armenia over 1996 against 26 over 1995. -0-<br>
<p>
     FRANCE IS CO-CHAIRMAN OF OSCE MINSK GROUP OF NAGORNO<br>
KARABAKH<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 8. (SNARK). Today, Levon Zurabian, Press<br>
Secretary of the Armenian President, informed journalists that<br>
under the instruction of Flavio Kotti, OSCE Chairman, France has<br>
been appointed on the post of Co-Chairman of OSCE Minsk<br>
conference of Nagorno Karabakh.<br>
     Germany and the US were among the pretenders on the post as<br>
well. Meanwhile, Armenia would appreciate any candidate, said<br>
Levon Zurabian adding that Armenia would agree with the<br>
appointment of any country-member of the Minsk group but not<br>
Turkey. According to Zurabian, Turkey can not be unbiased. -0-<br>
<p>
     ARMENIA'S PRESIDENT MEETS ERNST MULEMAN<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 8. (SNARK). Today, Levon Zurabian, Press<br>
Secretary of the Armenian President, said in an interview with<br>
journalists that President Levon Ter-Petrossian met Ernst<br>
Muleman, parliamentarian of Switzerland and head of the Swiss<br>
delegation to the European Parliament, who visited Armenia<br>
recently. During the meeting, the President said that both the<br>
membership of Armenia in the European Council and the membership<br>
of neighbouring newly independent countries is of great<br>
importance for Armenia. According to Levon Ter-Petrossian, the<br>
membership of the countries will promote additional<br>
responsibility, development of cooperation and democracy as well<br>
as boosting stability in Transcaucasus.<br>
     According to Zurabian, the main issue discussed during the<br>
meeting was the membership of Armenia in the European Council.<br>
Ernst Muleman noted that reporting and juridical delegations<br>
will visit Armenia shortly. The delegations should familiarize<br>
themselves with the situation in Armenia. In particular, the<br>
Armenian Legislation should meet the standards of the European<br>
Council.<br>
     Levon Ter-Petrossian assured the guest that Armenia is<br>
ready to provide the delegations with assistance and to review<br>
those legal documents which do not meet the standards of the<br>
European Council. -0-<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
