PRESS RELEASE<br>
<p>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
JANUARY 9, 1997<br>
<p>
THE AGBU NEW YORK SUMMER INTERN PROGRAM IS NOW ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS FOR ITS<br>
1997 SEASON<br>
<p>
Contact:  Talar Sesetyan<br>
<p>
AGBU New York Summer Intern Program<br>
31 W. 52nd Street<br>
New York, NY 10019<br>
(212) 765-8260<br>
(212) 765-5414 (fax)<br>
<p>
A Most Memorable Summer Opportunity for Undergraduate and Graduate Students<br>
<p>
The AGBU New York Summer Intern Program is seeking bright, young aspiring<br>
professionals to participate in its 1997 season.<br>
<p>
Qualified students are placed in summer intern positions in top New York City<br>
companies and institutions which match their fields of study and interest,<br>
plus partake in an array of educational, cultural, professional, and social<br>
programs designed exclusively for the program participants.  Students<br>
majoring in all fields may apply.  <br>
<p>
Application Deadline:  February 15, 1997<br>
<p>
The AGBU New York Summer Intern Program has placed interns at:<br>
<p>
*  Goldman Sachs &amp; Company<br>
*  The United Nations<br>
*  Merryll Lynch<br>
*  New York University Medical Center<br>
*  The Metropolitan Museum of Art<br>
*  Office of the Mayor of New York City<br>
*  New York City Law Department<br>
*  Price Waterhouse<br>
*  Fox Television<br>
*  Cosmopolitan<br>
*  Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher &amp; Flom<br>
<p>
For mor information and to request an application, please call Talar Sesetyan<br>
at (212) 765-8260.<br>
<p>
The AGBU New York Summer Intern Program is funded exclusively by the AGBU<br>
President's Club, a group of donors who sponsor a series of youth-oriented<br>
programs dedicated to the advancement of Armenian youth.<br>
