Armenia: Authorities Refuse To Re-register Opposition Party<br>
<p>
By Hrair Tamrazian<br>
<p>
Yerevan, 8 January 1997 (RFE/RL) - Armenia's Justice Ministry today<br>
refused to re-register the Dashnakzutune opposition party, which was<br>
banned more than two years ago.<br>
<p>
The party had applied to be registered again last August after making<br>
some changes in the party charter. But the Justice Ministry today said<br>
that it is not satisfied with the charter changes, and said the major<br>
obstacle for registering the party remained unchanged.<br>
<p>
The party was banned on grounds that there are many foreigners in the<br>
party's leadership, which violates Armenian law. This month, the new<br>
Prime Minister, Armen Sarkissian, met leaders of the Dashnak party (as<br>
it is commonly known) and promised that their case will be resolved<br>
soon. Our Yerevan correspondent reports the party's leadership had<br>
been optimistic that Government would lift the ban.<br>
<p>
<p>
 1996 Radio Free Europe / Radio Liberty, Inc.<br>
                                       All Rights Reserved.<br>
