<!-- body="start" -->
ATHENS, January 8 (Itar-Tass) - Armenia supports Cypriots' efforts  aimed<br>
at<br>
strengthening their security, visiting Armenian Foreign  Minister Alexander<br>
Arzumanyan said on Wednesday commenting on Cyprus'  decision to buy S-300<br>
surface-to-air missile systems from Russia.<br>
   The minister also stressed the necessity of further development of <br>
bilateral<br>
cooperation and called for Athens' support to Armenia in  international<br>
organisations.<br>
   ser/<br>
