<title>Groong Network: VOA/Turkey/Human Rights</title>
<h1>VOA/Turkey/Human Rights</h1>
Kevork K. Oskanian (<i>100436.3410@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 9 Jan 1997 03:04:03 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#302">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#302">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#302">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#302">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0303.html">Kevork K. Oskanian: "Armenia voices backing of Russia-Cyprus deal."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0301.html">nt-send@nt.arminco.com: "Noyan Tapan News (January 8)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
DATE=1/8/97<br>
TYPE=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<br>
NUMBER=2-208379<br>
TITLE=TURKEY/HUMAN RIGHTS (L)<br>
BYLINE=AMBERIN ZAMAN<br>
DATELINE=ANKARA<br>
CONTENT=<br>
VOICED AT: <br>
<p>
INTRO:  SCORES OF TURKISH SECURITY OFFICIALS WERE CHARGED <br>
WEDNESDAY WITH MANSLAUGHTER IN THE DEATHS OF 10 PRISONERS DURING <br>
RIOTS LAST YEAR IN A PRISON IN THE MAINLY KURDISH PROVINCE OF <br>
DIYARBAKIR.  FROM ANKARA, AMBERIN ZAMAN HAS THE DETAILS.<br>
<p>
TEXT:  TURKISH GOVERNMENT SOURCES CONFIRMED A TOTAL OF 65 <br>
SECURITY OFFICIALS FACE UP TO 16 YEARS IN PRISON IF CONVICTED ON <br>
CHARGES OF USING EXCESSIVE FORCE WHILE TRYING TO QUELL THE RIOTS.<br>
<p>
THE OFFICIALS -- WHO INCLUDE POLICE OFFICERS, PRISON WARDENS AND <br>
SPECIAL PARAMILITARY FORCES -- ALSO HAVE BEEN CHARGED WITH <br>
DERELECTION OF DUTY DURING THE DISTURBANCES AT THE DIYARBAKIR <br>
PRISON WHICH BEGAN LAST SEPTEMBER.<br>
<p>
THE RIOT WAS REPORTED TO HAVE STARTED AFTER THE PRISONERS TOOK <br>
ONE OF THE WARDENS HOSTAGE TO PROTEST LIVING CONDITIONS AT THE <br>
MAXIMUM SECURITY JAIL.  HUMAN RIGHTS OFFICIALS SAY 10 PRISONERS -<br>
ALL ETHNIC KURDS -- DIED AND SEVERAL OTHERS WERE SEVERELY BEATEN.<br>
<p>
A PARLIAMENTARY COMMITTEE FORMED TO INVESTIGATE THE RIOTS ALSO <br>
ACCUSED THE SECURITY FORCES OF CAUSING THE DEATHS OF THE INMATES.<br>
MOST OF THEM WERE SERVING SENTENCES FOR PROMOTING KURDISH <br>
SEPARATISM OR BEING LINKED TO THE OUTLAWED KURDISTAN WORKERS' <br>
PARTY -- THE P-K-K.  THE REBEL GROUP HAS BEEN FIGHTING SINCE 1984<br>
FOR A KURDISH HOMELAND CARVED MAINLY OUT OF SOUTHEAST TURKEY.<br>
<p>
HUMAN RIGHTS GROUPS HAVE WELCOMED THE COURT'S DECISION TO CHARGE <br>
THE SECURITY OFFICIALS.  THEY SAY IT IS EXCEEDINGLY RARE STATE <br>
OFFICIALS GET PUNISHED FOR ABUSES AND HUMAN RIGHTS OFFICIALS SAY <br>
SUCH VIOLATIONS ARE COMMON, ESPECIALLY IN THE MAINLY KURDISH <br>
SOUTHEAST REGION.<br>
<p>
// OPT //  THEY SPECIFY THE CASE OF METIN GOKTEPE, A LEFT WING <br>
JOURNALIST, WHO WAS ALLEGEDLY BEATEN TO DEATH BY A GROUP OF <br>
POLICE OFFICERS DURING A DEMONSTRATION IN ISTANBUL LAST YEAR.  <br>
HUMAN RIGHTS ORGANIZATIONS SAY THE OFFICERS IMPLICATED IN THE <br>
KILLING HAVE  NOT  YET BEEN CHARGED, ALTHOUGH THERE IS -- IN <br>
THEIR WORDS -- IRREFUTABLE EYEWITNESS EVIDENCE SHOWING THEY WERE <br>
RESPONSIBLE FOR GOKTEPE'S DEATH.  // END OPT //  (SIGNED) <br>
<p>
NEB/AZ/ADEN/CF<br>
<p>
08-Jan-97 11:22 AM EST (1622 UTC)<br>
NNNN<br>
<p>
Source: Voice of America<br>
.<br>
