"KEM" ENSEMBLE IN CONCERT IN ISTANBUL<br>
<p>
(ISTANBUL - "Lraper" 8/Jan/1997) - Chamber music ensemble "KEM" gave a<br>
concert in the Bezciyan Hall of the Armenian Cathedral in Istanbul on<br>
7 January at 18:00 hours. The Christmas event was organized by the<br>
Armenian Patriarchate.<br>
<p>
The "KEM" was organized on the initiative of Armen Ghukasian in 1980<br>
at the Artistic Center of Yerevan. The members of the ensemble are<br>
professional musicians who are performing also in the National Opera<br>
Theatre's Symphonic Orchestra and are solists of the Yerevan Chamber<br>
Orchestra. The ensemble was also permanently performing in the concert<br>
hall of the Contemporary Arts Gallery.<br>
<p>
In 1981 the ensemble took part in the Transcaucasian Festival of<br>
ensembles and got the first prize. It was on tours in Russia,<br>
Lithuania, Estonia and Latvia. The ensemble's performing style is<br>
greatky influenced by such great masters as Alexey Lubimov and Tatiana<br>
Grindenko. Since 1994, the ensemble bears the name "Kem" and enjoys<br>
the patronage of various church organizations.  The program of the<br>
ensemble usually includes works of the Armenian, German, French,<br>
Spanish, Chekh and Slovak, Austrian and other composers.<br>
<p>
The Christmas Concert in Istanbul, attended by His Beatitude Armenian<br>
Patriarch Karekin II, His Holiness Greek Orthodox Patriarch<br>
Bartholomew I and a crowd of some 500 people (Armenian and foreign<br>
clergymen, foreign diplomats, Armenian and Turkish intellectuals,<br>
community leaders and members) was a great success.  Armen Ghukasian<br>
(flute), Khosrov Yaghupian (violin), Ara Ghukasian (cello) and Suren<br>
Tanielian (violone) presented works of Mozart, Corelli, Marchand and<br>
Komitas.<br>
<p>
The concert will be repeated in the Saints Vartanants Church Hall on<br>
Friday, 10 January 1997, at 21:00 hours.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
