MISAK MEDZARENTS REMEMBERED IN ISTANBUL - <br>
<p>
(ISTANBUL - "Lraper" 8/Jan/1997) The 110th birth anniversary of the<br>
Western Armenian poet Misak Mezarents was celebrated in Istanbul.<br>
<p>
On 21 December a commemorative event had been organized in the<br>
Bezciyan Hall in Kumkapi by the joint efforts of the Armenian<br>
Patriarchate of Istanbul, the Parish Council of the Surp Astvadzadzin<br>
Cathedral in Kumkapi and the Getronagan Alumni Association in<br>
Istanbul. By 18.00 hours all 600 seats in the hall were occupied by<br>
the admirers of Medzarents, and many others followed the event,<br>
standing.<br>
<p>
The two MCs were Miss Carolyn Sariboyajian and Mr Hagop Mamigonian,<br>
both teachers in the Getronagan Lycee where Medzarents studied.The<br>
Headmistress of the Getronagan Lycee read a paper, in which she<br>
highlighted the place of Medzarents in Western Armenian<br>
literature. The second and main paper was delivered by an<br>
intellectual, Mrs Armine Yazdanian, who also taught in the Get-<br>
ronagan. Mrs Yazdanian presented a literary analysis of some of<br>
Medzarents' poems. Two very poignant letters addressed to Medzarents<br>
and written by the present students of the Lycee were read by Miss<br>
Narod Nayirian and Mr Mihran Tovmasian.  Mrs Ovsanna Kalender,<br>
director of the Getronagan Choir, and accompanied by pianist Mr Sevan<br>
Agoshian, sang two songs arranged from Medazrents' poems. Mrs Silva<br>
Gomigian then recited some 10 poems of Medzarents.<br>
<p>
The program ended with the final words of His Beatitude Patriarch<br>
Karekin II of Istanbul who presided over the event. Also present were<br>
His Graces Archbishops Tirayr Mardikian of Romania and Mesrob Mutafyan<br>
of the Patriarchal Religious Council.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
