PATRIARCHATE RECEPTION SUCCESSFUL EVENT<br>
<p>
(ISTANBUL - "Lraper" 8/Jan/1997) - The annual traditional reception<br>
given by the Armenian Patriarch of Istanbul was as usual a very<br>
successful event. The reception on 7 January at 20:00 hours at the<br>
audience hall of the Patriarchate was attended by His Holiness Greek<br>
Orthodox Patriarch Bartholomew I, bishops of sister churches, Armenian<br>
and Turkish intellectuals, American, German, Greek, Swedish, Swiss,<br>
Dutch, Danish, Israeli, Italian and other diplomats serving in<br>
Istanbul, and Armenian church members serving currently in the various<br>
commissions of the Armenian Patriarchate, the Armenian Cathedral of<br>
Kumkapi and the Surp Pergitch Armenian Hospital.<br>
<p>
The event was opened by the brief message of welcome and greetings<br>
spoken by His Beatitude Patriarch Karekin II of Istanbul, in Armenian<br>
and Turkish. Armenian food was served by ladies of the Armenian church<br>
community.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
