FIRE IN THE ARMENIAN PATRIARCHATE OF ISTANBUL - <br>
<p>
(ISTANBUL - "Lraper" 8/Jan/1997) Midnight of 30 December 1996 fire<br>
broke in the Armenian Patriarchate in Istanbul. The fire which began<br>
in the roof was caused by the storm which hit the chimney of the<br>
wooden structure. The Fire department of Istanbul was on the site in<br>
less than 10 minutes, and aided by the security officials, it was soon<br>
put out successfully. The damages are minor.<br>
<p>
His Beatitude Patriarch Karekin II of Istanbul, who was resting in his<br>
room on the third floor of the building suffered a minor bruise on his<br>
left shoulder as his head spinned because of the heavy smoke and fell<br>
on the floor.  The members of the Brotherhood of the Patriarchate were<br>
also in the building but were spared any injuries.<br>
<p>
The Armenian community once again felt it necessary to reconstruct the<br>
structure as it is but of stone. The church authorities decided to<br>
apply to the government for the necessaru permission.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
