PILGRIMAGE TO TOMB OF MEDZARENTS - <br>
<p>
(ISTANBUL - "Lraper" 8/Jan/1997) The students from various Armenian<br>
schools in Istanbul paid a pilgrimage to the tomb of Misak Medzarents<br>
in the historic Balikli cemetery, on the occasion of the 110th birth<br>
anniversary celebrations of the famous poet.<br>
<p>
The pilgrimage started from the Saint Gregory the Illuminator's Church<br>
adjacent to Getronagan Lycee in Ghalatia, where lies Patriarch<br>
Hovhannes Golod, the patron par excellence of Western Armenian<br>
literature. Approximately 100 students then walked all the way along<br>
the Sea of Marmara, past the Golden Horn, the Topkapi Palace, the<br>
Armenian Patriarchate and finally arrived at the Balikli cemetery<br>
after a walk that lasted nearly five hours. The students also fasted,<br>
and decided to have on them nothing but flowers for Medzarents and<br>
booklets of Medzarents poems.<br>
<p>
The Patriarchal Vicar Archbishop Mesrob Mutafyan joined the young<br>
pilgrims at the Zeytinburnu gates of the old city walls and walked<br>
with them towards the cemetery. Fr Varujan Terterian of Yerevan also<br>
joined the pilgrims.<br>
<p>
A memorial service was held at the grave site. The MC was Miss Silva<br>
Kuyumjian, headmistress of the Getronagan Lycee. Quite a few poems<br>
were recited here by the students. Archbishop Mesrob Mutafyan<br>
delivered a heartfelt message in which he characterized Medzarents as<br>
a remarkable student, who received education at foreign schools<br>
founded by Protestant missionaries from abroad, but who remained loyal<br>
to his people's traditions, culture and faith.<br>
<p>
A religious service was then held at the end of which the students<br>
laid hundreds of flowers on the tomb of Medzarents.<br>
<p>
The youths also visited the tombs of poet Garbis Janjikian, educator<br>
Verjin Deoshemejian, Catholicos Toros of Cilicia, artist Hagop Arad<br>
and others.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
