KAREKIN II GREETED SISTER CHURCHES ON DECEMBER 25 - (ISTANBUL -<br>
"Lraper" 8/Jan/1997) His Beatitude Patriarch Karekin II of Istanbul<br>
greeted the leaders of the sister churches on the occasion on<br>
Christmas celebrated on 25 December.<br>
<p>
The spiritual leader paid a patriarchal visit to the Syrian Orthodox<br>
Patriarchal Vicar in Istanbul His Grace Archbishop Mar Philixinos<br>
Yusuf Cetin on Dec 25 afternoon. There was a solemn entrance to the<br>
Syrian Orthodox cathedral followed by a reception in the church hall,<br>
where His Beatitude greeted the eminent members of the Syrian Orthodox<br>
community of Istanbul and Ankara. Karekin II said that the Syrian<br>
Orthodox Church was closest to the Armenian Church in doctrine and<br>
tradition. The vicar of the Armenian Patriarch and the chairman of the<br>
Patriarchal Religious Council, His Grace Archbishop Mesrob Mutafyan<br>
attended the Syriac Christmas liturgy the same morning and<br>
administered Holy Communion together with the Syrian Orthodox<br>
Archbishop as a sign of full communion in Christ.<br>
<p>
Patriarch Karekin II also paid a fraternal visit to His Holiness<br>
Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew I the same afternoon and expressed to<br>
him and the Greek Orthodox church community in Turkey his best wishes<br>
for Christmas.<br>
<p>
Next day, Patriarch Karekin II's vicar Archbishop M.  Mutafyan paid<br>
courtesy visits to His Excellency the Latin Bishop Louis Pelatre of<br>
the Roman Catholics in Istanbul and Ankara, and the leaders of the<br>
Anglican and Presbyterian churches in Istanbul.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
