<!-- body="start" -->
        ARMENIAN-RUSSIAN RELATIONS TO TAKE A NEW<br>
        QUALITY<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 07, ARMENPRESS.<br>
The Prime Minister of the Republic of Armenia Armen Sargsian met <br>
with the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the Russian <br>
Federation in the Republic of Armenia Andrey Urnov.<br>
The Prime Minister highly evaluated the results of his last visit to <br>
Moscow. He also thanked the Ambassador for organizing the meetings <br>
in Moscow on a high level. The Prime Minister stated that the <br>
Armenian-Russian relations will take a new quality after the <br>
arrangements made there. A closer cooperation, particularly in the <br>
fields of energy, industry and chemistry is expected in future. <br>
<p>
        PRIME MINISTER RECEIVED THE FIRST SECRETARY <br>
        OF THE COMMUNIST PARTY OF THE REPUBLIC OF ARMENIA<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 07, ARMENPRESS.<br>
The Prime Minister of the Republic of Armenia Armen Sargsian <br>
received the First Secretary of the Communist Party of the Republic of <br>
Armenia Sergey Badalian. Sergey Badalian appreciated the readiness of <br>
the government for dialogue. He presented his disposition concerning <br>
the political, social-economic situation of the republic.<br>
The Prime Minister Armen Sargsian mentioned that the government is <br>
elaborating a new program of social-political development. He <br>
suggested that the Communist Party come up with a proposal <br>
concerning social-political development. <br>
<p>
        VISIT OF THE PRIME MINISTER OF THE REPUBLIC OF <br>
        ARMENIA TO THE UNITED STATES<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 07, ARMENPRESS.<br>
The Prime Minister of the Republic of Armenia Armen Sargsian left for <br>
Washington DC. The purpose of his visit is to meet with the authorities <br>
of the World Bank and International Monetary Fund. The Prime <br>
Minister will discuss the main principles of the socio-economic <br>
development of the government of Armenia for the year 1997.<br>
        The Prime Minister will also meet the US state officials and <br>
businessmen, representatives of mass media, members of Armenian <br>
community. He will make a speech at the Harvard University. During <br>
the visit  two Armenian-American Business Centers are expected to be <br>
opened. The purpose of the centers is to promote business relation and <br>
investments.<br>
<p>
        LIST OF GOODS NEEDING CERTIFICATION EXPANDED<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 07, ARMENPRESS.<br>
Based on the Armenian Governments decision N417 on compulsory <br>
certification on products being imported to the Republic of Armenia, <br>
1994, and decision on making changes in the decision N417 of  the <br>
Government of the Republic of Armenia, July 4, 1996, new order is <br>
established for the goods being imported to Armenia. According to the <br>
new order, to the formerly established list of goods needing compulsory <br>
certification, spirituous drinks, beverages, vinegar and cigarettes, 20 <br>
more types of goods are added to the list including meat, milk, sugar, <br>
oil products, etc.<br>
According to Petros Dadayan, Deputy of the Agency of Customs, the <br>
importer should submit certificates obtained at foreign certification <br>
services. In case of failing to submit such certificates, the goods <br>
included in the list, will pass certification in the laboratories of  the <br>
Agency for Certification Limitations and Standardization.<br>
<p>
        NO VIOLATIONS ON ARMENIAN-AZERI BORDER<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 7, ARMENPRESS.<br>
According to the Armenian Defense Ministry, no incidents have been<br>
registered on the Armenian-Azeri border since the beginning of the<br>
year.<br>
<p>
        ARMENIAN AVIA BANK TO BE LIQUIDATED<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, JANUARY 7, ARMENPRESS.<br>
The Council of Central Bank of Armenia made a decision on liquidating the<br>
Hayaviabank (Armenian Avia Bank) and filing to the court for<br>
appointing a liquidation trustee.<br>
The Armenian Central Bank's decision N37, October 25, 1996, confirmed<br>
the insolvency of the bank, and by November 5 decision N48 the<br>
preliminary trusteeship of the bank began. During the trusteeship<br>
period, the bank did not recover from insolvency. The capital of the<br>
bank has decreased by 216.4 million drams, and at present its negative<br>
quantity is 895.5 million drams.<br>
Hayaviabank is the first bank to be liquidated according to the new<br>
law on bankruptcy of the banks. The case should be heard during a two<br>
week period.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
