Armenia/Azerbaijan: France To Co-Chair Nagorno-Karabakh Talks<br>
<p>
By Roland Eggleston<br>
<p>
Vienna, 7 January 1997 (RFE/RL) - The Organization for Security and<br>
Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) has named France the new co-chair of<br>
the deadlocked negotiations on the Nagorno-Karabakh dispute. The other<br>
co-chair is Russia, whose post is permanent. <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
