          Armenian premier leaves for Washington to meet WB ...<br>
 <br>
COMTEX NewswireSaturday, January 04, 1997  1:18:00 PM<br>
 <br>
 <br>
         YEREVAN, January 4 (Itar-Tass) - Armenian Prime Minister Armen<br>
Sarkisyan <br>
left for Washington on Saturday to hold talks with the leaders of the <br>
World Bank and the International Monetary Fund. <br>
   These international economic organisations play an important role in the <br>
implementation of Armenia's economic development, Sarkisyan said on <br>
Friday. <br>
   According to the prime minister's press service, during the visit, he <br>
will meet with representatives of the U.S. Administration and the <br>
Armenians who live in the United States. <br>
