<!-- body="start" -->
        PRESIDENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF ARMENIA RECEIVED REPRESENTATIVE OF =<br>
THE RUSSIAN FEDERATION<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 30, ARMENPRESS.<br>
On December 27, the President of the Republic of Armenia Levon=20<br>
Ter-Petrosian received the Special Representative of the Russian=20<br>
Federation Yury Yukalov. The Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs of=20<br>
the Republic of Armenia Vardan Oskanian and the Ambassador=20<br>
Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the Russian Federation in the=20<br>
Republic of Armenia Andrey Urnov  were present during the=20<br>
meeting. The sides discussed the current state of the Karabagh=20<br>
conflict resolution.=20<br>
<p>
        WORLD BANK REPRESENTATIVES ARE SATISFIED WITH THE ROAD REPAIR WORK =<br>
IN ARMENIA<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 30, ARMENPRESS.<br>
During the year 1996, 183 km of road have been repaired in=20<br>
Armenia instead of  261.3 km planned by the Road Repair Project,=20<br>
particularly 84.5 km have been asphalted and surface work of 98.5=20<br>
km have been done. The project is being implemented by of the=20<br>
World Bank credit.=20<br>
Nevertheless, the quality of the work satisfies the requirements. There=20<br>
have been only 8.11 km of non-quality surface work and 0.53 km of=20<br>
non-quality asphalted roads which the Office of the Road Repair=20<br>
Project did not appreciate. The daily supervision of the quality and=20<br>
the quantity of the work is implemented by the Finnish advisory firm =20<br>
*FinRoad*. The representatives of the World Bank are satisfied with=20<br>
the work.<br>
Next year the roads to Meghry and Georgia will be repaired.<br>
<p>
        NEW CREDIT PROJECT IN AMRENIA APPROVED BY WORLD BANK<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 30, ARMENPRESS.<br>
The World Bank has approved a credit of =2416.75 mln to Armenia=20<br>
which will be used to finance the project of increasing enterprises.=20<br>
The purpose of this project is to increase the private sector-strengthen=20=<br>
<p>
banks and industrial enterprises. The credit will be given on=20<br>
beneficial terms, i.e., duration for 35 years and 0.75 % yearly=20<br>
payment.<br>
        Armenia has been member of the World Bank since 1992.=20<br>
Since then world Bank implemented 9 projects worth of =24262.25 mln.=20<br>
in  Armenia.<br>
<p>
<p>
        CREDIT FOR DEVELOPMENT OF ENTERPRISES RATIFIED<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 30, ARMENPRESS.<br>
The Board of Executive Directors of the World Bank ratified the credit<br>
given to Armenia for the program of the development of enterprises.<br>
The aim is to give financial support to private enterprises,<br>
to strengthen financial institutions and to contribute to the growth of =<br>
the<br>
investments in the private sector and the possibilities for exporting.<br>
The =2416.75 million loan will be redeemed in 35 years. The redemption<br>
process will begin in 10 years.<br>
<p>
        PROBLEMS OF THE LOCAL SELF-GOVERNMENT BODIES DISCUSSED<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 30, ARMENPRESS.<br>
On December 27, in the American University of Armenia, a meeting<br>
the main problems of the local self-government bodies took place.<br>
The meeting was organized by the Armenian National Movement<br>
party. The President of the National Assembly of the Republic of<br>
Armenia Babken Ararktsian, Vice President of the National<br>
Assembly Ara Sahakian and Karapet Roubinian, Ministers and other<br>
officials participated in the meeting.<br>
The leader of the Armenian National Movement Ter Husik Lazarian<br>
pointed out in his speech that the purpose of the meeting is to<br>
discuss specific problems of the local self-government bodies.<br>
The participants of the meeting pointed out in their speeches<br>
that the imperfections in the law on local self-government. They<br>
also discussed financial and other problems of the local<br>
self-government bodies.<br>
The Vice President of the National Assembly of the Republic of<br>
Armenia Karapet Roubinian pointed out that the local<br>
self-government bodies are in their initial phase of development,<br>
which explains the numerous problems they encounter.<br>
Talking about the budget of the local self-government bodies, Mr.<br>
Roubinian said that the sources of income in the local budgets<br>
are not clearly defined, the state and community property is not<br>
separated.<br>
Talking about the law on local self-government bodies, Mr.<br>
Roubinian stated that the law does not define the powers of the<br>
local authorities in terms of the struggle against violations of<br>
laws. The actions of the local authority figures are governed by<br>
the presidential decrees, and not by the law. That could cause<br>
certain disagreements between the governors of the marzes<br>
(provinces) and the local authorities.<br>
The Minister of Local Self-Government Galust Gamazian in his<br>
speech pointed out that the documents regulating the local<br>
self-government bodies had not been passed before the November 10<br>
local self-government elections. Now, the government of the<br>
Republic of Armenia has established a committee which will work<br>
on these documents. He also informed that in order to get<br>
acquainted personally with the situation, the Prime Minister of<br>
the Republic of Armenia Armen Sargissian will visit various<br>
regions of the country until February 1997.<br>
The speech of the Vice President of the National Assembly of the<br>
Republic of Armenia Ara Sahakian had more political flavor to it.<br>
Mr. Sahakian pointed out the important political events which<br>
took place in Armenia this year: presidential elections, new<br>
government, and local self-government elections. Mr. Sahakian<br>
also emphasized the role of the Armenian National Movement in<br>
these processes and pointed out the differences between the<br>
party and the opposition. According to Mr. Sahakian, the Armenian<br>
National Movement has a high sense of responsibility for the<br>
destiny of the country and the nation, while the opposition,<br>
whose formal leader is the head of the National Democratic Union,<br>
and the real leader is the Armenian Revolutionary Federation,<br>
preferred to violate the laws and the Constitution of the<br>
Republic of Armenia. These leaders throw their political<br>
ambitions to the street, and the street dictates its own ways of<br>
political struggle.<br>
In this situation, the local self-government bodies should<br>
involve the people in the process of local self-government and<br>
have high sense of responsibility for the people. He called on<br>
local authority figures to cooperate with all their opponents<br>
in the election.<br>
At the end of the meeting, Ter Husik Lazarian introduced the text<br>
of the resolution. The resolution includes all the points and<br>
suggestions voiced during the meeting. The resolution points out<br>
that the local self-government is a necessary condition for the<br>
development of democracy. The resolution also informed about the<br>
creation of the Association of Communities of Armenia.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
