Pan-Armenian Science Review Volume 4 Number 1<br>
******************************************<br>
           <br>
    Call for Papers     Call for Papers     Call for Papers<br>
<p>
<p>
Dear Paacs and Groong netters<br>
<p>
The Pan-Armenian Science Review is compiling a Special Issue on Information<br>
Technology and Applications to be released in March/April 1997.<br>
<p>
Authors in the Applied Physics, Engineering, Computer Sciences, Electronics<br>
and related disciplines are invited to submit articles on various aspects of<br>
the following topics:<br>
<p>
* Modern Information Technology<br>
* Coding and Compression techniques<br>
* Modern Satellite Telephone Systems<br>
* Telecommunications Protocols (CDMA and GSM)<br>
* Information Storage Systems<br>
* WWW and its Applications <br>
* Uses of Electronic Mailing and Various Protocols<br>
* Novel Communications Methods<br>
<p>
The articles should not be more that 4 A4 sides and should reach the Society<br>
not later that end of February 1997.<br>
<p>
The articles should ideally be sent on IBM-pc floppy diskette and processed<br>
with one of the popular Word processing packages i.e. Micro-Soft Word,<br>
Word-Perfect and Ami-Pro. <br>
<p>
Preferred format is English however Armenian text will also be accepted.<br>
<p>
Authors who are not members of the Society will get a complimentary copy of<br>
the publication.<br>
<p>
<p>
