PRESS RELEASE				FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
December 28, 1996<br>
<p>
	U.S. FEDERAL JUDGE GRANTS REQUEST TO WITHDRAW<br>
		LAW SUIT AGAINST LIBARIDIAN<br>
<p>
YEREVAN - On December 20, 1996, United States District Judge Michael <br>
B. Mukasey of the Southern District Court of New York granted <br>
plaintiffs' motion to withdraw their complaint against Jirair Libaridian <br>
before the case could even be heard by the judge.  This brought to an <br>
abrupt end a lawsuit which was started against the Senior Advisor to <br>
President Levon Ter-Petrossian of Armenia last October with much noise <br>
and vindictiveness.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
