Dear Groong readers,<br>
<p>
GROONG Articles are for Groong's audience only. Redistribution of<br>
Groong postings to any other media, including but not limited to other<br>
mailing lists and Usenet bulletin boards, is strictly prohibited<br>
without prior written consent from Groong's Administrator.<br>
<p>
The GROONG mailing list's news are believed to be from reliable sources.<br>
However, no responsibility by the List's Administation or by USC is<br>
assumed for inaccuracies. No statements made on this mailing list are to<br>
be construed as recommended by the List's Administation or by USC. Nor<br>
does the List's Administation or USC necessarily endorse the contents,<br>
providers, opinions or information presented.<br>
<p>
Currently, all content providers post information on a voluntary basis.<br>
As such, no obligation by the List's Administation or by USC is assumed,<br>
to continue or to maintain these services.<br>
<p>
We're pleased that you read Groong and follow news related to Armenian<br>
matters around the globe on a daily basis. We hope to continue to<br>
provide you with news and announcements, and we always aim to increase<br>
the breadth of the information provided here.<br>
<p>
Regards,<br>
<p>
Asbed<br>
<pre>
