<p>
     CELEBRATION OF CATHOLIC CHRISTMAS HELD AT CENTER OF GERMAN<br>
CULTURE IN YEREVAN<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 23. (SNARK). Carola Muller-Holtcamper, German<br>
Ambassador to Armenia, informed Snark that she endorses and<br>
appreciates the activity of the Center of German Culture in<br>
Armenia. She attended the December 23 celebration of the<br>
Catholic Christmas that was held at the Center of German Culture<br>
in Yerevan.<br>
     The center conducts free courses of the German language.<br>
     The German Union supporting the Germans residing world-wide<br>
provides assistance to the Center of the German Culture in<br>
Yerevan.<br>
     The German Community operating in Yerevan from 1992<br>
includes 75 families. According to Alexander Yaskorskiy, Head of<br>
the Community, 1,000 Germans currently reside in Armenia.<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
      ARMENIAN-IRANIAN COOPERATION TO BE STRENGTHENED AND<br>
      FURTHERED<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 26. (SNARK). Hassan Habibi, the First Vice<br>
President of the Islamic Republic of Iran (IRI), that arrived in<br>
Yerevan with an official visit, stated at today's meeting with<br>
the members of the Armenian National Assembly that currently the<br>
relations between Armenia and Iran are based on friendship and<br>
mutual understanding.<br>
      The IRI First Vice President noted some significant<br>
achievements of the Armeno-Iranian cooperation. For instance,<br>
Mr. Habibi underlined and highly appreciated the following<br>
facts: establishment (1994) of the Armeno-Iranian joint economic<br>
commission in Yerevan; the exchange of the delegations<br>
consisting of the Armenian and Iranian high rank authorities;<br>
the construction (1995) of a bridge over the River of Arax; air<br>
communications connecting Yerevan and Tehran; signing of<br>
important documents and agreements related to the Armeno-Iranian<br>
cooperation in the field of culture, sciences and education as<br>
well economic issues such as investments, support and<br>
improvement of trade affairs, prevention of double taxation,<br>
transportation and communications, agriculture, industry and<br>
health protection.<br>
     Currently the projects related to the construction of a<br>
pipeline for transportation of gas from the IRI to Armenia,<br>
establishment of the direct phone communications, construction<br>
of phone net station connecting Meghri (Armenia) and Marand<br>
(Iran), selling of liquified gas to Armenia, construction of the<br>
oil processing plants in Armenia, and the construction of the<br>
joint electric power plant generator over the River of Arax are<br>
being developed and discussed, reported the IRI First Vice<br>
President.<br>
     Underlying the importance of the stability in the region,<br>
the Iranian guest noted that the world super states try to<br>
interfere in interior affairs of the countries of the region,<br>
which posses highly developed culture coming from dawn of<br>
centuries and higher level of civilization.<br>
     The speaker of Armenia's National Assembly, Babken<br>
Ararktsian, stated that the visit of Mr. Habibi to Armenia will<br>
support and strengthen the Armeno-Iranian cooperation and<br>
symbolize new step of the furthering of the Armenian-Iranian<br>
affairs.<br>
<p>
<p>
      PRESIDENT OF REPUBLIC OF MOUNTAINOUS KARABAKH MET WITH<br>
      CO-CHAIRMAN OF OSCE MINSK GROUP<br>
<p>
STEPANAKERT, DECEMBER 26. (SNARK). Today, the President of the<br>
Republic of Mountainous Karabakh, Mr. Robert Kocharian, met  with<br>
the visiting to Stepanakert Co-Chairman of the OSCE Minsk Group,<br>
Russia's Ambassador Youri Youkalov. The meeting was closed for<br>
others.  -0-JK<br>
<p>
      PRIME MINISTER OF ARMENIA MEETS WITH IRAN'S FIRST VICE<br>
      PRESIDENT<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 26. (SNARK). Today, the Prime Minister of Armenia,<br>
Armen Sarkissian, met with the visiting to Armenia First Vice<br>
President od the ISlamic Republic of Iran, Hassan Habibi. There is an<br>
unused potential and significant economic and juridical basis in the<br>
Armenia-Iranian cooperation, stated the Armenian Prime Minister.<br>
     Mr. Sarkissian expressed his hope that the visit of the high<br>
rank Iranian official will further the affairs between two countries.<br>
-0-JK<br>
<p>
    DEPUTY CHAIRMAN OF ARMENIA'S CENTRAL BANK MEET'S WITH<br>
    DIRECTOR GENERAL OF IRANIAN CENTRAL BANK'S DEPARTMENT ON<br>
    INTERNATIONAL OPERATIONS AND DIRECT OF DEVELOPMENT OF<br>
    EXPORTS IRANIAN BANK<br>
<p>
YEREVAN, DECEMBER 26. (SNARK). The Press Office of Armenia's<br>
Central Bank informed Snark that today the Deputy Chairman of<br>
the Central Bank of Armenia, Armen Darbinian, met with the<br>
Director General of the Iranian Central Bank's Department on<br>
International Operations, Hussein Majnuri, and the Director of<br>
the Development of Exports Iranian Bank, Novruz Konzadi.<br>
      The issues related to the development of cooperation<br>
between Armenia's and Iran's bank structures were discussed at<br>
the meeting. The importance of the banks' role in servicing of<br>
the Armenian-Iranian trade and economic affairs.<br>
      Representatives of Armenia's commercial banks participated<br>
at the meeting as well.<br>
<p>
<p>
         OFFICIAL RATES OF ARMENIA'S CENTRAL BANK<br>
