<!-- body="start" -->
                  Wind of gale force damages Armenian regions.<br>
 <br>
COMTEX NewswireSunday, December 29, 1996 11:12:00 AM<br>
 <br>
 <br>
         YEREVAN, December 29 (Itar-Tass) -  Wind of gale force and scattered <br>
rains make weather in Yerevan this Christmas. <br>
   Part of the Armenian capital does not have electricity, several <br>
apartment houses are ruined, roofs of hospitals and a kindergarten are <br>
torn off and some monuments are damaged. Fires broke out in four <br>
boroughs of Yerevan and several settlements nearby. Telephone <br>
communication with adjoining settlements is broken. According to <br>
preliminary reports of the Kapan mayor's office, the damage of local <br>
houses is estimated at 16 million Armenian drams (about 40,000 <br>
dollars). <br>
   Electricity supply to Alaverdi, Stepanavan and about 30 populated <br>
localities is broken. Hundreds of power line poles are damaged in <br>
Stepanavan alone. Roofs are torn off, trees are fallen by the wind. <br>
   Measures are being taken to repair the damage, reports the Armenian <br>
governmental press service. There is no loss of life. <br>
   bic/ <br>
   <br>
Copyright 1996<br>
