<!-- body="start" -->
DATE=12/29/96<br>
TYPE=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<br>
NUMBER=2-208033<br>
TITLE=CHECHNYA / WITHDRAWAL / S&amp;L<br>
BYLINE=PETER HEINLEIN<br>
DATELINE=MOSCOW<br>
 <br>
CONTENT=<br>
VOICED AT: <br>
<p>
INTRO:  RUSSIAN OFFICIALS SAY THE WITHDRAWAL OF COMBAT TROOPS <br>
FROM CHECHNYA HAS BEEN COMPLETED, PAVING THE WAY FOR REGIONAL <br>
ELECTIONS NEXT MONTH.  V-O-A'S PETER HEINLEIN IN MOSCOW REPORTS <br>
MANY OF THE TROOPS FACE DIFFICULT CONDITIONS AS THEY MOVE TO <br>
TEMPORARY DUTY STATIONS. <br>
<p>
TEXT:  RUSSIAN NEWS AGENCIES SUNDAY SAID UNITS OF THE 205TH <br>
MOTORIZED RIFLE BRIGADE WERE FLYING OUT OF THE KHANKALA AIR BASE,<br>
A FEW KILOMETERS FROM THE CHECHEN CAPITAL, GROZNY.  THE 205TH WAS<br>
THE LAST COMBAT OUTFIT REMAINING OF THE ESTIMATED 50 THOUSAND <br>
RUSSIAN TROOPS SENT TO CHECHNYA TWO YEARS AGO TO QUELL A <br>
SEPARATIST UPRISING.  <br>
<p>
THE ITAR-TASS NEWS AGENCY QUOTES MILITARY OFFICIALS AS SAYING <br>
ONLY A FEW ENGINEERING AND TRANSPORT UNITS WILL REMAIN IN THE <br>
BREAKAWAY REGION.  PRESIDENT BORIS YELTSIN HAS ORDERED ALL TROOPS<br>
PULLED OUT BEFORE JANUARY 27TH, WHEN REGIONAL ELECTIONS ARE <br>
SCHEDULED. <br>
<p>
RUSSIAN NATIONAL SECURITY ADVISER IVAN RYBKIN TOLD RADIO RUSSIA <br>
SUNDAY THE TROOP WITHDRAWAL LEAVES RESPONSIBILITY FOR CHECHNYA <br>
COMPLETELY IN THE HANDS OF REBEL COMMANDER ASLAN MASKHADOV.  <br>
<p>
MR. MASKHADOV IS ONE OF AT LEAST FIVE CANDIDATES RUNNING FOR THE <br>
CHECHEN PRESIDENCY.  <br>
<p>
UNDER AN AGREEMENT THE REBEL COMMANDER WORKED OUT WITH MR. <br>
RYBKIN'S PREDECESSOR, FORMER SECURITY CHIEF ALEXANDER LEBED, <br>
RUSSIA WILL PULL OUT ALL TROOPS BEFORE THE ELECTION.  IN RETURN, <br>
THE REBELS AGREED TO POSTPONE ANY DECISION ON CHECHNYA'S FUTURE <br>
STATUS FOR FIVE YEARS.  <br>
<p>
THE ACCORD WAS SIGNED LAST AUGUST, AFTER NEARLY A MONTH OF <br>
FIGHTING IN WHICH THE VASTLY-OUTNUMBERED REBELS INFLICTED A <br>
HUMILIATING DEFEAT ON THE RUSSIAN FORCES.  AT THE TIME, MR. LEBED<br>
ESTIMATED THE WAR HAD CLAIMED AS MANY AS 100 THOUSAND LIVES, MOST<br>
OF THEM CIVILIANS. <br>
<p>
IN A RELATED DEVELOPMENT, RUSSIAN TELEVISION REPORT TROOPS <br>
WITHDRAWING FROM CHECHNYA ARE BEING FORCED TO LIVE IN TENTS IN <br>
SUB-FREEZING TEMPERATURES BECAUSE THERE IS NO PLACE TO HOUSE <br>
THEM.  AN INDEPENDENT T-V REPORT SHOWED SHIVERING SOLDIERS <br>
STANDING IN A SNOWSTORM IN THE SOUTHERN STAVROPOL REGION, WHERE <br>
THEY ARE TEMPORARILY STATIONED.  <br>
<p>
LOCAL OFFICIALS SAY STAVROPOL RESIDENTS ARE DONATING FOOD, WARM <br>
CLOTHING AND MEDICINE TO THE TROOPS.  THE REGION HAS BEEN  HIT BY<br>
A SEVERE WINTER SNOWSTORM IN RECENT DAYS.  TELEVISION REPORTS <br>
INDICATED THE TEMPERATURE IN STAVROPOL FELL TO MINUS-20 DEGREES <br>
CELSIUS SUNDAY.  <br>
<p>
(SIGNED)<br>
<p>
NEB / PH / BD / WOD<br>
<p>
29-Dec-96 2:25 PM EST (1925 UTC)<br>
NNNN<br>
<p>
Source: Voice of America<br>
.<br>
