        INAUGURATION OF THE PRESIDENT OF THE<br>
NAGORNO-KARABAGH REPUBLIC<br>
<p>
 STEPANAKERT, DECEMBER 24, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 On December 23, the National Assembly of Nagorno-Karabagh<br>
 Republic held a special session during which the inauguration of<br>
 the President of NKR took place.<br>
 Robert Kocharian gave an oath to be the guarantor of NKR<br>
 Constitution and legislation, the security of NKR citizens,<br>
 their rights and freedoms; to follow the policy aimed at<br>
 securing the unification of Nagorno-Karabagh Republic, Armenia<br>
 and the Armenian Diaspora.<br>
 The President of NKR stated that OSCE Lisbon Summit's results<br>
 showed that we can overcome any serious difficulties in case we are<br>
 unified.<br>
 The Leader of Artsakh Diocese Bishop Pargev Martirosian blessed<br>
 the President. The Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Republic<br>
 of Armenia Alexander Arzumanian and the President of the Central<br>
 Bank of Armenia Bagrat Asatrian were present during the<br>
 ceremony.<br>
<p>
        PAGER SERVICE AVAILABLE IN YEREVAN<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 24, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Yesterday, Armenian Telephone (ArmenTel) offered its services of<br>
 Radiosearch Paging system to people in Yerevan. The equipment is<br>
 supplied by the US company "MOTOROLA".<br>
 The Prime Minister Armen Sargsian congratulated the Ministry of<br>
 Communication with the work done. He mentioned that first of all<br>
 people in government and businessmen need this type of service.<br>
 Later general public may also find it useful. The Prime Minister<br>
 hoped that in the future digital telephone stations will be<br>
 opened as well.<br>
<p>
        MINISTER OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS OF THE REPUBLIC OF ARMENIA<br>
  ALEXANDER ARZUMANIAN VISITS THE NAGORNO-KARABAGH<br>
REPUBLIC<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 24, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 On December 22 and 23, the Minister of Foreign Affairs of the<br>
 Republic of Armenia Alexander Arzumanian visited the<br>
 Nagorno-Karabagh Republic.<br>
 During the visit, Mr. Arzumanian met with the President of the<br>
 Nagorno-Karabagh Republic Robert Kocharian, the Prime Minister<br>
 Leonard Kocharian, the Minister of Foreign Affairs Arkadi<br>
 Ghukasian, and the Minister of Defense Samvel Babayan.<br>
 During these meetings, the sides discussed various issues<br>
 related to the negotiation of the Karabagh conflict resolution<br>
 and the results of the OSCE Lisbon Summit.<br>
<p>
        GOVERNMENT SESSION DECIDES TO ESTABLISH AGRARIAN<br>
AGENCIES<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 24, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Yesterday, took place a session of the Government of the<br>
 Republic of Armenia. The Prime Minister Armen Sargissian<br>
 presided.<br>
 During the session, the Government passed a decision to<br>
 establish state agrarian inspections (agencies). The Government<br>
 also decided to found the "Official Bulletin of the Republic of<br>
 Armenia" and the "Bulletin of Departmental Normative Acts"<br>
 periodical. The Government also defined penalties for those<br>
 organizations who do not make the required contribution to the<br>
 Pensions and Employment Fund.<br>
<p>
        CARGO TERMINAL CONSTRUCTION STARTED<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 24, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The construction of the cargo terminal of the Zvartnots airport<br>
 in Yerevan has started. The construction works are conducted by<br>
 a contract with the American "Billhartert" organization. The<br>
 contract value is $15,400,000.<br>
 Based on another contract with the Dutch Cargo Service Center,<br>
 Armenian specialists will take special training courses in the<br>
 Netherlands. When the construction is over, this Dutch firm will<br>
 run the Zvartnots cargo terminal for a year.<br>
