<title>Groong Network: Armenia/Powergen:  Privatization</title>
<h1>Armenia/Powergen:  Privatization</h1>
Areg Gharabegian (<i>Areg_Gharabegian@parsons.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 27 Dec 1996 14:37:11 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#225">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#225">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#225">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#225">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0226.html">Armen Martirossyan: "From Armenpress Homepage"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0224.html">mrw@arminco.com: "Revised 'Some impressions from HH Karekin I's Press Conf.'"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
---------------------------------- Forwarded ----------------------------------<br>
From: GUNN@USITA.GOV (Trevor Gunn) at INTERNET<br>
Date: 12/19/96 8:22AM<br>
To: Areg Gharabegian at PARLOS1<br>
Subject: Armenia/Powergen:  Privatization<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
COURTESY:  American Embassy- Yerevan, Armenia<br>
SUBJECT: (IMI) ARMENIA PRIVATISES EIGHT HYDRO-POWER<br>
PLANTS THROUGH INTERNATIONAL TENDER.<br>
<p>
ATTENTION U.S. MANUFACTURERS/SUPPLIERS/INVESTORS<br>
(ENERGY SECTOR)<br>
<p>
-------<br>
SUMMARY<br>
-------<br>
<p>
ARMENIA HAS BEGUN A PILOT PROGRAM OF ENERGY ASSET<br>
PRIVATIZATION, SELLING OFF EIGHT SMALL HYDROELECTRIC<br>
PLANTS.  THE PILOT PROGRAM IS MEANT TO PROVIDE A<br>
LEARNING CURVE FOR INVESTORS TO GET INVOLVED IN ARMENIA<br>
WITH MINIMAL RISK EXPOSURE, AND TO HELP ARMENIA BETTER<br>
MANAGE WITH LARGER-SCALE PRIVATIZATION COMING SOON.<br>
<p>
MAJOR PARTS OF THE 2,500-MEGAWATT STATE-OWNED ELECTRIC<br>
POWER SECTOR, AND OTHER MAJOR STATE-OWNED ENERGY ASSETS<br>
SUCH AS THE GAS COMPANY ARMGASPROM, ARE ON THE OFFICIAL<br>
LIST OF STATE-OWNED ASSETS TO BE PRIVATIZED IN THE<br>
1996/1997 PROGRAM.<br>
<p>
ARMENIA HAS UNDERTAKEN SUBSTANTIAL REFORM IN THE<br>
ELECTRIC POWER SECTOR BY SEPARATING THE VERTICALLY<br>
ELECTRIC UTILITY SECTOR INTO GENERATION, TRANSMISSION,<br>
AND DISTRIBUTION, BY RAISING TARIFFS, AND INCREASING<br>
COLLECTIONS DRAMATICALLY ON THE CONSUMER SIDE.<br>
<p>
INDEPENDENT POWER IN ARMENIA IS FACILITATED BY A<br>
LICENSING LAW, AND FOREIGN INVESTOR LAW, ALLOWING FREE<br>
REPATRIATION OF PROFITS, FREELY FLUCTUATING EXCHANGE<br>
RATES, 100% FOREIGN OWNERSHIP OF BUSINESSES IN ARMENIA,<br>
AMONG OTHER PROVISIONS.  AN ENERGY LAW IS EXPECTED TO<br>
BE PASSED BY PARLIAMENT IN EARLY 1997.<br>
<p>
THE PILOT PRIVATIZATION PROGRAM STARTS THE PROCESS OF<br>
COMPETITIVE BIDDING FOR THE EIGHT SMALL PLANTS,<br>
TOTALING APPROXIMATELY 12 MEGAWATTS OF CAPACITY.<br>
FOREIGN COMPANIES AND INDIVIDUALS MAY PARTICIPATE IN<br>
THE PROCESS ON EQUAL TERMS AS LOCAL ARMENIAN CITIZENS<br>
AND COMPANIES.<br>
<p>
MINIMUM PRICES SET FOR THE PLANTS ARE CONSISTENT WITH<br>
THE OVERALL RISK PROFILE, IN OTHER WORDS, MINIMUM BID<br>
PRICES HAVE BEEN SET RELATIVELY LOW.  IT IS HOPED THAT<br>
FOREIGN INVESTORS MAY SEEK TO TEAM UP WITH LOCAL GROUPS<br>
SO EXPERIENCE IN INDEPENDENT POWER PLANT DEVELOPMENT<br>
AND MANAGEMENT IS BROUGHT INTO THE COUNTRY.<br>
WHOLESALE ELECTRIC TARIFFS ARE FIXED BY AN<br>
INTERMINISTERIAL  TARIFF-SETTING COMMITTEE.  IPP RATES<br>
HAVE A FLOOR EQUAL TO THE AVERAGE WHOLESALE ELECTRIC<br>
PRICE OF GENERATORS SELLING INTO THE TRANSMISSION<br>
NETWORK, CURRENTLY SET AT APPROXIMATELY 2.2 CENTS.<br>
RETAIL ELECTRIC RATES ARE CURRENTLY THE EQUIVALENT 3.4<br>
CENTS/KWH, AND ARE SCHEDULED TO GO UP TO 4.2 CENTS IN<br>
1997.<br>
<p>
TARIFF REFORM IS ONE OF AGENDA ITEMS IN ELECTRICITY<br>
SECTOR REFORM WHICH IS BEING CLOSELY WATCHED AND<br>
ASSISTED BY MULTI-LATERAL GROUPS SUCH AS THE WORLD<br>
BANK, THE EUROPEAN BANK FOR RECONSTRUCTION AND<br>
DEVELOPMENT, AND BI-LATERAL AID AND DEVELOPMENT<br>
ORGANIZATIONS, SUCH AS US AGENCY FOR INTERNATIONAL<br>
DEVELOPMENT.<br>
<p>
THE HYDROELECTRIC PLANTS INCLUDED IN THE PILOT PROGRAM<br>
ARE IN VARIOUS STATES OF CAPABILITY RANGING FROM FULLY<br>
FUNCTIONAL TO GREENFIELD SITES IN WHICH NEW EQUIPMENT<br>
MAY BE DEPLOYED.  THE MINISTRY OF ENERGY IS IN CHARGE<br>
OF ENERGY PRIVATIZATION PROCESS AND IS COORDINATING<br>
WITH FOREIGN PARTIES.<br>
<p>
TENDERS FOR PRIVATIZATION OF THE EIGHT HHP WERE<br>
PUBLISHED IN LOCAL NEWSPAPERS.  AFTER A WINNER IS<br>
ANNOUNCED, THE MINISTRY OF PRIVATIZATION AND FOREIGN<br>
INVESTMENT WILL SIGN A PRIVATIZATION AGREEMENT WITH THE<br>
WINNER WITHIN TWO MONTHS PERIOD.  AFTER THAT, THE<br>
ARMENIAN MINISTRY OF AGRICULTURE AND THE MINISTRY OF<br>
ENERGY WILL SIGN WITHIN 30 DAYS AGREEMENTS (FOR AT<br>
LEAST 10 YEARS) WITH THE WINNER FOR SUPPLY OF THE<br>
NECESSARY AMOUNT OF WATER, AND FOR PURCHASE AND/OR<br>
TRANSMISSION OF THE ELECTRICITY.<br>
<p>
PRELIMINARY INFORMATION PACKAGES IN ENGLISH MAY BE<br>
OBTAINED BY CONTACTING:<br>
<p>
THE MINISTRY OF ENERGY<br>
MR. GAREN GALUSTYAN,<br>
DEPUTY MINISTER OF ENERGY (SPEAKS ENGLISH)<br>
2ND GOVERNMENT BLDG.<br>
REPUBLIC SQUARE<br>
YEREVAN 375010 ARMENIA<br>
TEL: (374-2)525-205<br>
FAX: (374-2)151-687<br>
<p>
AND<br>
<p>
"ARMAVENI" CONSULTING COMPANY<br>
(MR. STEPAN MANTARLYAN, CHAIRMAN)<br>
3RD GOVERNMENT BLDG., ROOM 323, YEREVAN 375010 ARMENIA,<br>
TEL: (374-2)589-201, 589-286<br>
FAX: (374-39)07197<br>
<p>
IMPORTANT NOTE: THE EMBASSY HAS BEEN INFORMED, THAT IN<br>
ORDER TO ATTRACT FOREIGN INVESTORS THE MINISTRY OF<br>
ENERGY IS CONSIDERING EXTENSION OF THE BID SUBMISSION<br>
DEADLINE FOR ALL THE EIGHT HHP UP TO APRIL 17.<br>
EXCHANGE RATE AS OF DEC 13, 1996 WAS USD L/DRAM 440.<br>
<p>
