<!-- body="start" -->
        60TH ANNIVERSARY OF ENERGY SYSTEM<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 23, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 On December 20, a meeting dedicated to the 60-th anniversary of<br>
 Energy<br>
 system of Armenia took place. During the meeting the Minister of<br>
 Energy Gagik Martirosian congratulated the energetics with the Day of<br>
 Energetics. He mentioned that this year is also the anniversary of<br>
 several<br>
 electric power plants of Armenia. The Minister noted the role<br>
 of the energy system in the stable development of the Republic's<br>
 economy,<br>
 the mutually beneficial cooperation with foreign organizations and<br>
 the<br>
 solution of future problems.<br>
 Mr. Martirosian mentioned the importance of the fact that the energy<br>
 crisis has been overcome. He also noticed that several new sources of<br>
 energy<br>
 will be implemented in the near future, like the new block of Hrazdan<br>
 Thermal Electric Power Plant, the construction of the Iran-Yerevan<br>
 high<br>
 voltage electric wire-line, and the Herher Hydro-Electric Station in<br>
 the South of Armenia. The far future projects include the<br>
 construction of the Iran-Armenia gas-line, the Hydro-Electric<br>
 Stations in<br>
 Meghry, Shnogh. It is supposed that after the reforms, by th year<br>
 2000, the energy system of Armenia will be able to produce 12 billion<br>
 kw/h<br>
 energy (as in 1988).<br>
<p>
        STATEMENT OF THE MINISTRY OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS OF THE REPUBLIC<br>
        OF ARMENIA<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 23, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 On December 16-17, 1996, the Second Conference of the Ministers of<br>
 Environment of Central Asian, Caucasian and Balkan Republics was<br>
 held in Istanbul, with the participation of the delegation of the<br>
 Republic of Armenia, headed by the Minister of Environment Mr. Souren<br>
 Avetissian. Also participating in the Conference were 13 other<br>
 delegations, including the self-proclaimed "Turkish Republic of<br>
 Northern Cyprus" and the representatives of the Former Yugoslav<br>
 Republic of Macedonia represented under the name of the "Republic of<br>
 Macecdonia." At the end of the Conference a joint declaration was<br>
 adopted which was also signed by the Minister of Environment of the<br>
 Republic of Armenia.<br>
 On this occasion, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of<br>
 Armenia informs that pursuant to the decisions of the United Nations<br>
 and other international organizations, the Republic of Armenia<br>
 recognizes the Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia by its<br>
 internaitonally accepted name, and hopes that all the problems<br>
 related to the name of the  republic could be resolved by<br>
 UN sponsered peaceful negotiations on the basis of mutual<br>
 compromise.<br>
 Furthermore, the Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of<br>
 Armenia declares that the Republic of Armenia remains faithful to its<br>
 frequently stated position that the Cyprus problem must be resolved<br>
 according to the resolutions of the United Nations, and it does not<br>
 recognize any other government than the legitimate authorities of the<br>
 Republic of Cyprus.<br>
 THe Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Armenia declares<br>
 that the Ministry of Envirnoment was not authorized to sign on behalf<br>
 of the Republic of Armenia any document which also bears the<br>
 signature of the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus" - an entity<br>
 that is not a subject of international law.<br>
 While welcoming the regional cooperation on environmental issues, the<br>
 Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Armenia considers the<br>
 politicization of conference devoted to such important issues<br>
 unacceptable.<br>
<p>
        PRESIDENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF ARMENIA LEVON TER-PETROSSIAN<br>
        MEETS WITH THE CATHOLICOS GAREGIN I<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 23, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 On December 21, the President of the Republic of Armenia Levon<br>
 Ter-Petrossian received the Catholicos of All Armenians, His Holiness<br>
 Garegin I. The Catholicos informed the President about his official<br>
 visit to Vatican and Italy, the meetings with the Roman Pope John<br>
 Paul II<br>
 and  the President of Italy Oscar Luidgi Scalfaro. During the<br>
 meetings issues concerning the celebration of the 1700-th anniversary<br>
 of the adoption of Christianity in Armenia were discussed.<br>
<p>
        80% OF APARTMENTS PRIVATIZED IN ARMENIA<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 23, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 As of today, about 80% of the 396.360 apartments in Armenia have been<br>
 privatized. 80% of apartments have been privatized in Yerevan as<br>
 well. Now the privatization process has slowed down, because the<br>
 housing fund became the local self-government bodies' possession.<br>
 On November 18 of the current year, the National Assembly of the<br>
 Republic of Armenia passed a law, which prolonged the privatization<br>
 process until June 30, 1997.<br>
<p>
        PRIME MINISTER MEETS WITH THE DELEGATION OF THE DEMOCRATIC<br>
        PARTY OF ARMENIA<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 23, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Yesterday, the Prime Minister of the Republic of Armenia Armen<br>
 Sargissian met with the Chairman of the Democratic Party of Armenia<br>
 Aram Sargissian, and other party's officials.<br>
 During the meeting, the party officials informed the Prime Minister<br>
 about the party's viewpoints on the socio-political and economic<br>
 situation in Armenia. They expressed their support of Government's<br>
 program of socio-economic development and readiness to participate in<br>
 the its implementation.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
