The Association of Armenian Information Professionals (AAIP) is pleased <br>
to announce the publication of Volume 3, Number 2, of its <br>
bilingual/biannual serial, Journal of the Association of Armenian <br>
Information Professionals (JAAIP).<br>
<p>
Table-of-Contents Highlights:<br>
<p>
-	The DICTA Series of Electronic Dictionaries<br>
	by Stepan Stepanian<br>
-	The Role of Armenian Libraries in the Democratization Process<br>
	by Anna Shirinian (in Eastern Armenian)<br>
-	Infopolitics, Technophilia, Technophobia, et Cetera<br>
	by Shahe Navasart Sanentz<br>
-	AAIP Activities Report<br>
	by Anie S. Kalayjian<br>
-	AAIP at ALA:  Panel Explores International Dimensions of 	<br>
	Information Age<br>
<p>
For information on how to order, to join AAIP, or to submit manuscripts <br>
to JAAIP:<br>
<p>
AAIP<br>
139 Cedar Street<br>
Cliffside Park, NJ 07010<br>
<p>
T:  (201) 941-2266<br>
F:  (201) 941-5110<br>
E:  aaipnet@aol.com<br>
<p>
The deadline for the next issue:  May 1, 1997.<br>
<p>
Back issues are available, while supplies last.<br>
