<title>Groong Network: VOA/Turkey/Iran</title>
<h1>VOA/Turkey/Iran</h1>
Kevork K. Oskanian (<i>100436.3410@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 25 Dec 1996 07:46:36 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#216">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#216">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#216">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#216">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0217.html">nt-send@nt.arminco.com: "Noyan Tapan News (December 25)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0215.html">nt-send@nt.arminco.com: "Noyan Tapan News (December 24)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
DATE=12/23/96<br>
TYPE=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<br>
NUMBER=2-207875<br>
TITLE=U-S/TURKEY/IRAN (S ONLY)<br>
BYLINE=VICTOR BEATTIE<br>
DATELINE=WASHINGTON<br>
CONTENT=<br>
VOICED AT: <br>
<p>
INTRO:  THE UNITED STATES HAS VOICED ITS CONCERN OVER A NUMBER OF<br>
ECONOMIC AGREEMENTS INCREASING TRADE BETWEEN IRAN AND NATO ALLY <br>
TURKEY, WHICH NOW HAS AN ISLAMIC-LED GOVERNMENT.  V-O-A'S VICTOR <br>
BEATTIE REPORTS THE STATEMENT COMES AS A U-S DEFENSE OFFICIAL <br>
SAYS A RUSSIAN-BUILT SUBMARINE IS NOW ON ITS WAY TO THE PERSIAN <br>
GULF FOR DELIVERY TO THE IRANIAN NAVY:<br>
<p>
TEXT:  U-S STATE DEPARTMENT SPOKESMAN GLYN DAVIES SAYS THE <br>
AGREEMENTS, TOTALING TWO BILLION DOLLARS, WERE SIGNED AS IRANIAN <br>
PRESIDENT ALI AKBAR HASHEMI RAFSANJANI ENDED A VISIT TO ANKARA <br>
SATURDAY:<br>
<p>
                     ///DAVIES ACTUALITY///<br>
<p>
         WE REMAIN CONCERNED BY ALL EFFORTS TO INTENSIFY <br>
         COOPERATIVE RELATIONS WITH IRAN UNTIL TEHRAN REFORMS ITS<br>
         UNACCEPTABLE INTERNATIONAL POLICIES.<br>
<p>
                       ///END ACTUALITY///<br>
<p>
THE UNITED STATES HAS LONG OPPOSED WHAT IT CALLS IRAN'S SUPPORT <br>
OF TERRORISM, OPPOSITION TO THE MIDEAST PEACE PROCESS AND PURSUIT<br>
OF THE ACQUISITION OF WEAPONS OF MASS DESTRUCTION:<br>
<p>
                     ///DAVIES ACTUALITY///<br>
<p>
         THE TURKISH GOVERNMENT KNOWS WELL OUR CONCERNS.  WE <br>
         COMMUNICATE THEM TO THEM FREQUENTLY AND WE WILL MAINTAIN<br>
         AN ACTIVE DIALOGUE WITH TURKEY.<br>
<p>
                       ///END ACTUALITY///<br>
<p>
THE STATE DEPARTMENT OFFICIAL DID NOT INDICATE WHETHER A U-S LAW <br>
THAT CALLS FOR SANCTIONS AGAINST COMPANIES INVESTING MORE THAN <br>
40-MILLION DOLLARS IN THE IRAN WILL BE ENFORCED.<br>
<p>
MR. DAVIES REPEATED THE U-S POSITION THE BILATERAL AGREEMENTS ARE<br>
NOT IN THE U-S INTEREST.  LAST WEEK, SECRETARY OF STATE WARREN <br>
CHRISTOPHER DENOUNCED TEHRAN AS A DANGEROUS FORCE IN THE WORLD, <br>
ONE THE UNITED STATES MUST ACT TO CONTAIN.<br>
<p>
MEANWHILE, A U-S DEFENSE OFFICIAL SAYS A THIRD RUSSIAN KILO-CLASS<br>
DIESEL-POWERED SUBMARINE IS BEING DELIVERED TO IRAN AS PART OF <br>
ITS PROGRAM TO MODERNIZE ITS NAVAL FORCES.  (SIGNED)<br>
<p>
NEB/VB/KL<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
.  <br>
<p>
23-Dec-96 9:52 PM EST (0252 UTC)<br>
NNNN<br>
<p>
Source: Voice of America<br>
.<br>
