<title>Groong Network: Pan-Armenian Acad. Sci. Soc. News</title>
<h1>Pan-Armenian Acad. Sci. Soc. News</h1>
Dr Manook Soghomonian (<i>manook_s@moose.co.uk</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 23 Dec 1996 13:39:15 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#205">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#205">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#205">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#205">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0206.html">ASBAREZ-ON-LINE: "ASBAREZ-ON-LINE [12-23-96]"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0204.html">Chavoush@aol.com: "Armenian News 12/22/96"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
------------------------------------<br>
For PAACS and Groong netters<br>
------------------------------------<br>
News Summary<br>
          &amp;<br>
Christmas Greetings<br>
------------------------------------<br>
<p>
Dear fellow Armenians, colleagues and friends,<br>
<p>
The end of 1996 marks the end of the third successful year in the life of<br>
the Pan-Armenian Academic and Scientific Society.<br>
The Society which started off  mere technical club, in April 1994, between<br>
Yerevan, Lancaster and Brunel Universities, has grown steadily into a global<br>
grouping encompassing 3 continents and myriads of scientific and non<br>
scientific disciplines.<br>
<p>
The Society's newsletter 'Pan-Armenian Science Review' is steadily becoming<br>
a recognise scientific publication in its own right and as members have<br>
notices it now carries a verity of technical as well as very descriptive<br>
materials. <br>
The recent issue of the Science Review Volume 3 number 3, carries articles<br>
on the architecture, computer science, psychology and law and the next issue<br>
focuses on the science of Information thecnology and its applications<br>
<p>
The message of the Society is, as it has always been, very simple and its<br>
ambitions very clear: to form cooperative links between technical as well as<br>
non-technical professionals around the world to give a lending hand to<br>
Armenia and to mankind. Slowly but surely this message is getting through<br>
and the responses that we have received have been very encouraging.<br>
<p>
Over the last year the Society has managed to launch its own scientific<br>
bulletin board (PAACS), create World Wide Web site and compile a world data<br>
bank of Armenian professional around the world.<br>
Moreover, the Society, through the efforts of  Prof. Markarian at Lancaster<br>
University, has managed to secure a large research fund for a project with<br>
the Institute of Radio-Physics in Ashtarak, Armenia. <br>
The task at hand is by no means completed and just over the horizon the<br>
Society is planning an Armenian Science  day in London.<br>
<p>
On behalf of the Society I would like to wish all fellow Armenians around<br>
the world a very healthy, happy and a prosperous new year, and hope to be<br>
able to make newer friends in the future. Furthermore I would like to thank<br>
all the members of the Society, in USA, UK, Canada and Armenia for their<br>
continued support.<br>
<p>
With best regards<br>
<p>
Dr Manook Soghomonian<br>
<p>
