Dear Groong and Hayastan readers,<br>
<p>
We have reached 11% participation in our drive to fund a subscription<br>
to Noyan Tapan (NT). We have currently 126 readers who have pledged<br>
support ranging from $5 - $250, and we are close to our goal.<br>
<p>
I'll make a last call for your participation, and I will close the<br>
fund drive next Friday, Dec. 28, hopefully with a successful ending.<br>
If you can, please come forward and help.<br>
<p>
My access to a terminal will be very sporadic until next friday, so<br>
please be patient with my slow replies to your email, which I will<br>
read.<br>
<p>
Thank you all who have already helped, and best wishes for the holidays<br>
to all readers.<br>
<p>
Asbed<br>
<pre>
--
Groong/Hayastan List Administrator	| Internet: groong-request@usc.edu
University of  Southern California	|	    hayastan-request@usc.edu
1020 W. Jefferson Blvd.			|
Los Angeles, CA 90089-0251		|
<p>
<p>
---------------- The original proposal is below. -----------------------
	Proposal for funding of Noyan Tapan Acquisition.
<p>
Dear Hayastan and Groong readers,
<p>
We've been in touch with Noyan Tapan (NT) to acquire their news on a daily
basis for Groong. As you may already know, NT is based in Armenia and
sells its news service for a fee.
<p>
NT came forward voluntarily during September's elections in Armenia and
informed us with up-to-the-minute news and events for altruistic reasons.
We appreciated their work; we think that their news service is very
informative and timely, and we'd like to read more of it, and regularly.
<p>
Noyan Tapan has requested a fee of $250/month for a specially prepared
"Groong Edition" daily bulletin, and has sent us many days' worth of
samples. I'm attaching one day's worth below for your perusal and
judgement. I feel the fee is reasonable and well worth it.
<p>
In addition to improving our quality of news here on Groong, and being
better informed on Armenia and the Caucasus region in general, our
subscription to Noyan Tapan will be an explicit statement of support
and approval for free and independent media in Armenia.
<p>
As the daily readers of Groong News, there's only you to turn to, to fund
such a project. Therefore I'm asking all interested parties to come
forward with any amount of donation to fund the next 12 months' worth of
Noyan Tapan reception on Groong.
<p>
We need to raise $3000 for this. Groong has 1100 members and Hayastan
has 350. If 100 members come forward with $30 each, we're there! If
more members come forward, then we will arrange to receive as many
more months of daily Noyan Tapan as we have money for.  And if we
don't come up with the required funds, then I will assume that we're
not interested in receiving Noyan Tapan daily.
<p>
I ask that you send me email, with your pledge amount, which I will
tally. The deadline for this initial drive is December 25. If we're
well on the way, I'll extend the deadline a bit and continue reminding
very often, as I feel that this is a very worthy service and would
enhance our news from Armenia greatly.  I will of course update the
list very regularly of our progress. In fact, I can tell you that we
already have $260 from just 4 Groong readers!
<p>
My goal at the moment is to receive NT news daily for all of 1997.
<p>
Send no money now. Once final amounts are tallied, I'll inform the lists
where to send checks and who to write it out to. As far as trusting that
your (our) funds will be well used, I assure you that every penny will
be spent on this project, and there will be not a penny of administrative
overheard (I'll deal with that).
<p>
I hope to hear from you very soon. Please help if you can.
<p>
Regards,
<p>
Asbed
<p>
----------------------- Sample NT for Groong bulletin ------------------
<p>
NOYAN TAPAN DAILY INFORMATION BULLETIN
                       FOR GROONG READERS
<p>
                       November 26, 1996
<p>
    -------------------------------------------------------
                 (c) 1996, All Rights Reserved
    Material in this publication  may not be  reproduced in
    any form  without  permission,  nor  may it  be sold or
    otherwise transferred to a third party. The information
    in this publication is provided for groong members.
<p>
    The materials included in the bulletin are less than the
    whole amount of  the daily news.  The full  daily  issue
    is available only for the subscription basis.
<p>
    If you wish to receive the full issue of the  Noyan Tapan
    daily information, please contact:
                   E-mail: nt@nt.arminco.com
          Tel &amp; Fax: (3742) 52-42-79, (3742) 56-19-05
<p>
   ----------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------
