<title>Groong Network: From Armenpress homepage</title>
<h1>From Armenpress homepage</h1>
Armen Martirossyan (<i>martiros@scf-fs.usc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 20 Dec 96 14:43:24 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#192">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#192">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#192">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#192">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0193.html">ASBAREZ-ON-LINE: "ASBAREZ-ON-LINE [12-20-96]"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0191.html">nt-send@nt.arminco.com: "Noyan Tapan News (December 20)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
        MEETINGS WITH PRESIDENT OF REPUBLIC OF ARMENIA<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 20, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Yesterday, the President of the Republic of Armenia, Levon<br>
Ter-Petrosian<br>
 received Baroness Caroline Cox. She is the Head of the mission of<br>
 humanitarian assistance to Nagorno Karabakh and Armenia organized<br>
by<br>
 the International Christian Solidarity Organization. The mission includes<br>
 the foundation of an Orthopaedic Clinic and a Rehabilitation Center<br>
 in Stepanakert. Medical equipment and other forms of humanitarian<br>
 assistance are also part of the mission.<br>
        The President thanked the Baroness for the moral and material<br>
 assistance that she displays to Nagorno Karabakh. He also informed<br>
 her about the current state of the Karabagh conflict resolution<br>
 process. From her side, Caroline Cox told that she and<br>
 parliamentarians of a number of countries will continue defending the<br>
 right of the people of Nagorno Karabakh in international sphere.<br>
<p>
         BRIEFING OF THE PRIME MINISTER ARMEN SARGSIAN<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 20, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 The Prime Minister of Armenia Armen Sargsian had a briefing after the<br>
 regular session of the Government. Armen Sargsian informed about the<br>
 results of his non-official visit to Great Britain. During the visit<br>
 he met the British Foreign Minister, Minister of Trade, the officials<br>
 of Administration of Science and Culture and other officials. The<br>
 second purpose of the visit was the discussions with the Directors of<br>
 European Bank of Reconstruction and Development. The Prime Minister<br>
 had meetings with the President and the Deputy President of the Bank,<br>
 during which projects being implemented in Armenia were discussed.<br>
 Future projects were also touched upon. The sides had discussed such<br>
 issues as the construction of the 5-th block of Hrazdan Thermal<br>
 Electric Power Plant, the cargo terminal in the Zvartnots airport in<br>
 Yerevan, wholesale market and other problems. The speaker mentioned<br>
 that during the last two years there were some obstacles with the<br>
 European Bank concerning the Nuclear Power Plant. It was possible to<br>
 settle these issues in a diplomatic manner.<br>
 The Prime Minister announced that the construction of the 5-th block<br>
 of Hrazdan Thermal Electric Power Plant has been stopped for almost a<br>
 year. It turned out that the remaining money is not enough to finish<br>
 the work. The European Bank has hired two organizations to examine<br>
 the situation. Transition period, unexpected expenses on<br>
 transportation and the like were identified as the main causes of the<br>
 situation. As to the Prime Minister, the solution must be looked for<br>
 in macroeconomic perspective, i.e. the problem of the whole economy<br>
 and not only the problem of Hrazdan must be taken into consideration.<br>
 To finish the project there will be a need for as much funds as was<br>
 previously invested. As to the Prime Minister, the process of<br>
 privatization must be continued and speeded with the help of the<br>
 newly established Ministry of Privatization.<br>
<p>
         ARMENIAN NUCLEAR POWER PLANT IS 20 YEARS OLD<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 20, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Yesterday, the Director of the Armenian Nuclear Power Plant, Suren<br>
 Azatian held a press conference on the occasion of the 20th<br>
 anniversary of the plant. During the press conference, Mr. Azatian<br>
 informed that in the last 20 years the plant has produced 47 bln.<br>
 kilowatt-hour of electricity. Currently, the plant is working with a<br>
 370 megawatt energetic capacity. According to the Director, the plant<br>
 is environmentally clean, and the amount of radiation and various<br>
 waste products thrown in the environment does not exceed the allowed<br>
 norms.<br>
 The Armenian Nuclear Power Plant is the only one in the region. It<br>
 actively cooperates with various international organizations. The<br>
 plant is a member of various important international organizations<br>
 and forums.<br>
<p>
        VARIOUS NEW ORGANIZATIONS AND PUBLICATIONS REGISTERED<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 20, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Today, the Ministry of Justice of the Republic of Armenia has<br>
 registered four new magazines, two bi-weekly publications, seven<br>
 weekly newspapers, one radio company, four TV programs, and a<br>
news<br>
 agency.<br>
 The Ministry also registered the by-laws of the Caucasian Center of<br>
 Iranian Studies, various federations, "Lore" group of rescuers from<br>
 Stepanavan (city in the north of Armenia), the branch of the Russian<br>
 Popular Fund, and two French Armenian charitable organizations.<br>
<p>
        PROBLEMS OF ETHNIC MINORITIES OF ARMENIA DISCUSSED<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 20, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Today, a session of the Armenian Union of Nations took place, in the<br>
 hall of the Association of Cooperation and Cultural Relations with<br>
 Foreign Countries. During the session, the President of the Union V.<br>
 Chatoyev informed the present about the activities of the<br>
 organizations in the two years of its existence.<br>
 The participants of the session discussed the issue of establishing a<br>
 cultural center of the Union. The participants also emphasized the<br>
 importance of a state organization which will deal with the problems<br>
 of ethnic minorities in Armenia.<br>
<p>
        ASSOCIATION OF THE MEANS OF MASS MEDIA ESTABLISHED IN<br>
ARMENIA<br>
<p>
 YEREVAN, DECEMBER 20, ARMENPRESS.<br>
 Today, the Association of the Means of Mass Media was established in<br>
 Armenia.<br>
 The purpose of this newly created organization is the enhancement of<br>
 free speech, democracy and pluralism of opinions in Armenia, as well<br>
 as the creation of favorable legal and economic conditions for the<br>
 operation of mass media means.<br>
 Heads of 22 means of mass media of the Republic of Armenia<br>
 participated in the founding meeting of the Association, which took<br>
 place today. During the meeting, the participants passed the<br>
 Association's charter and elected its governing bodies.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
